00:09:39.234 --> 00:09:41.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah!

00:09:41.160 --> 00:09:41.970 align:middle line:90%
Everything.

00:09:41.970 --> 00:09:42.500 align:middle line:90%
You have to.

00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:42.820 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Exactly.

00:09:42.820 --> 00:09:43.480 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:09:43.480 --> 00:09:43.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Exactly.

00:09:43.980 --> 00:09:45.770 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: See, there's
always this what's

00:09:45.770 --> 00:09:46.811 align:middle line:90%
most important principle?

00:09:46.811 --> 00:09:48.140 align:middle line:90%
What's the silver bullet?

00:09:48.140 --> 00:09:50.905 align:middle line:84%
And there isn't one because
it really is a system,

00:09:50.905 --> 00:09:53.740 align:middle line:84%
and I would say there's
about 25 things in the book.

00:09:53.740 --> 00:09:57.530 align:middle line:84%
There's the first 25
principles that are a system.

00:09:57.530 --> 00:09:59.530 align:middle line:84%
It's like you can't make
a cake with only wheat,

00:09:59.530 --> 00:10:02.540 align:middle line:84%
or only with eggs, are only
with yeast, or whatever.

00:10:02.540 --> 00:10:06.120 align:middle line:84%
So it's a system,
and a system, I

00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:08.840 align:middle line:84%
define it as something that
always works as long as you

00:10:08.840 --> 00:10:10.310 align:middle line:90%
work the system the same way.

00:10:10.310 --> 00:10:13.675 align:middle line:84%
If you have a recipe for
your grandmother's apple pie,

00:10:13.675 --> 00:10:15.800 align:middle line:84%
if you always preset
the oven correctly,

00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:18.030 align:middle line:84%
put in the right stuff,
don't use white sugar,

00:10:18.030 --> 00:10:20.870 align:middle line:84%
use brown sugar-- no today,
we'd use something else.

00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:21.370 align:middle line:90%
Agave.

00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:22.484 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Not sugar.

00:10:22.484 --> 00:10:23.350 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Yeah.

00:10:23.350 --> 00:10:27.689 align:middle line:84%
But the point being that,
just real quick, you

00:10:27.689 --> 00:10:29.230 align:middle line:84%
have to be clear
about what you want.

00:10:29.230 --> 00:10:31.450 align:middle line:84%
You have to take 100%
responsibility for your life.

00:10:31.450 --> 00:10:34.240 align:middle line:84%
You have to create a
vision of what it is.

00:10:34.240 --> 00:10:35.749 align:middle line:90%
You have to break it into goals.

00:10:35.749 --> 00:10:38.040 align:middle line:84%
You have to believe it's
possible, not just for someone

00:10:38.040 --> 00:10:39.740 align:middle line:90%
else, but for you.

00:10:39.740 --> 00:10:42.090 align:middle line:84%
Then you have to have
a plan, a strategy.

00:10:42.090 --> 00:10:43.950 align:middle line:84%
Now your strategy will
evolve and unfold,

00:10:43.950 --> 00:10:46.200 align:middle line:84%
but yo have to at least
see the first few steps.

00:10:46.200 --> 00:10:48.070 align:middle line:84%
I use the metaphor
of at night, you

00:10:48.070 --> 00:10:49.459 align:middle line:84%
don't need to see
the whole path,

00:10:49.459 --> 00:10:51.750 align:middle line:84%
you just need the next 200
yards, which your headlights

00:10:51.750 --> 00:10:52.610 align:middle line:90%
will illuminate.

00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:54.200 align:middle line:84%
But when you drive
that 200 yards,

00:10:54.200 --> 00:10:55.950 align:middle line:90%
the next 200 yards shows up.

00:10:55.950 --> 00:10:57.550 align:middle line:84%
If you don't know
what to do, go find

00:10:57.550 --> 00:10:59.100 align:middle line:90%
someone who's already done it.

00:10:59.100 --> 00:11:04.730 align:middle line:84%
I was in Texas getting my makeup
on before some morning TV show.

00:11:04.730 --> 00:11:07.375 align:middle line:84%
As I always do, I said
to the cosmetologist,

00:11:07.375 --> 00:11:11.049 align:middle line:90%
I said what's your dream?

00:11:11.049 --> 00:11:13.090 align:middle line:84%
She said, oh, I want to
own my own salon someday.

00:11:13.090 --> 00:11:14.290 align:middle line:90%
I said, it's great.

00:11:14.290 --> 00:11:15.914 align:middle line:84%
What are you doing
to make that happen?

00:11:15.914 --> 00:11:16.940 align:middle line:90%
She said, nothing.

00:11:16.940 --> 00:11:18.398 align:middle line:84%
I said, that's a
terrible strategy.

00:11:18.398 --> 00:11:21.460 align:middle line:90%


00:11:21.460 --> 00:11:22.380 align:middle line:90%
I said, why nothing?

00:11:22.380 --> 00:11:23.921 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
I don't know what

00:11:23.921 --> 00:11:25.200 align:middle line:90%
to do to open my own salon.

00:11:25.200 --> 00:11:27.270 align:middle line:84%
So I said, let me tell
you a radical idea.

00:11:27.270 --> 00:11:28.862 align:middle line:84%
Go find someone
who owns a salon.

00:11:28.862 --> 00:11:29.820 align:middle line:90%
Ask them what they did.

00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:31.512 align:middle line:84%
She went, oh,
that's really good.

00:11:31.512 --> 00:11:32.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What's my first step?

00:11:32.720 --> 00:11:33.428 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Yeah.

00:11:33.428 --> 00:11:36.424 align:middle line:84%
And so you got to take
what's the first step?

00:11:36.424 --> 00:11:38.090 align:middle line:84%
You got to surround
yourself with people

00:11:38.090 --> 00:11:41.240 align:middle line:84%
that are positive so you have
a positive support group.

00:11:41.240 --> 00:11:42.740 align:middle line:84%
Get someone to hold
you accountable,

00:11:42.740 --> 00:11:44.340 align:middle line:84%
whether it's an
accountability partner.

00:11:44.340 --> 00:11:45.720 align:middle line:84%
Every morning you
and I would talk,

00:11:45.720 --> 00:11:48.136 align:middle line:84%
and say what are the five
things you're going to do today?

00:11:48.136 --> 00:11:49.300 align:middle line:90%
Practice the rule of five.

00:11:49.300 --> 00:11:53.580 align:middle line:84%
Do five things every day to
move you toward your core goal.

00:11:53.580 --> 00:11:55.860 align:middle line:90%
Then take action.

00:11:55.860 --> 00:11:58.350 align:middle line:84%
Respond to feedback, because
every action doesn't work.

00:11:58.350 --> 00:11:59.780 align:middle line:84%
Most people never
ask for feedback

00:11:59.780 --> 00:12:01.910 align:middle line:84%
because they're afraid of
what they're going to hear.

00:12:01.910 --> 00:12:04.360 align:middle line:84%
I ask my wife once a week, on
a scale of 1 to 10, how would

00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:05.370 align:middle line:90%
you rate our relationship?

00:12:05.370 --> 00:12:06.865 align:middle line:84%
I'm not always thrilled
with the answer.

00:12:06.865 --> 00:12:07.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's brave!

00:12:07.850 --> 00:12:09.550 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Most
people don't ask.

00:12:09.550 --> 00:12:11.580 align:middle line:84%
But I'm the only one
who can improve it.

00:12:11.580 --> 00:12:14.360 align:middle line:84%
If I don't ask her, she's told
the women in the nail salon,

00:12:14.360 --> 00:12:16.165 align:middle line:90%
the line at Gelson's, whatever.

00:12:16.165 --> 00:12:17.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's right!

00:12:17.390 --> 00:12:19.305 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: So you got
to ask, and then you

00:12:19.305 --> 00:12:21.430 align:middle line:84%
got to respond to the
feedback, re-vector,

00:12:21.430 --> 00:12:24.490 align:middle line:84%
change course, persevere,
and never give up, and then

00:12:24.490 --> 00:12:25.352 align:middle line:90%
give thanks.

00:12:25.352 --> 00:12:27.810 align:middle line:84%
If you do those things in that
order-- and use affirmations

00:12:27.810 --> 00:12:30.268 align:middle line:84%
and visualization, which I left
out there, right before you

00:12:30.268 --> 00:12:34.540 align:middle line:84%
take action-- that's
a system that works.

00:12:34.540 --> 00:12:37.570 align:middle line:84%
Let's say this is a 10
number combination lock,

00:12:37.570 --> 00:12:39.160 align:middle line:90%
and you only know eight numbers.

00:12:39.160 --> 00:12:41.040 align:middle line:84%
I don't care how many
times you reconfigure

00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:42.660 align:middle line:84%
those eight numbers,
it still won't

00:12:42.660 --> 00:12:43.910 align:middle line:90%
work cause you're missing two.

00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:44.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So you need a formula.

00:12:44.590 --> 00:12:46.436 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: You need
a formula, yeah.

00:12:46.436 --> 00:12:48.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You said
something very important.

00:12:48.200 --> 00:12:50.810 align:middle line:84%
You said about
taking responsibility

00:12:50.810 --> 00:12:53.955 align:middle line:90%
for your goals or your actions.

00:12:53.955 --> 00:12:56.710 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Well, taking
responsibility for the results

00:12:56.710 --> 00:12:57.400 align:middle line:90%
you produce.

00:12:57.400 --> 00:12:58.894 align:middle line:90%
You don't blame anyone else.

00:12:58.894 --> 00:12:59.685 align:middle line:90%
You don't complain.

00:12:59.685 --> 00:13:00.518 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's huge.

00:13:00.518 --> 00:13:01.250 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: 100%.

00:13:01.250 --> 00:13:02.849 align:middle line:90%
And that's a big one.

00:13:02.849 --> 00:13:04.390 align:middle line:84%
That's the first
chapter in the book.

00:13:04.390 --> 00:13:05.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah-hah.

00:13:05.500 --> 00:13:08.355 align:middle line:84%
So taking responsibility for
even if you have failures

00:13:08.355 --> 00:13:10.980 align:middle line:84%
around it, there's usually some
reason where it might have been

00:13:10.980 --> 00:13:14.310 align:middle line:84%
a should instead of I would,
or something like that,

00:13:14.310 --> 00:13:16.727 align:middle line:84%
but it's somewhere buried in
your limiting beliefs, right?

00:13:16.727 --> 00:13:17.434 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Yeah.

00:13:17.434 --> 00:13:19.000 align:middle line:84%
It's buried in your
limiting beliefs,

00:13:19.000 --> 00:13:20.410 align:middle line:84%
or it's buried in
the fact that you

00:13:20.410 --> 00:13:22.910 align:middle line:84%
didn't know what you were doing
and you didn't study enough.

00:13:22.910 --> 00:13:24.740 align:middle line:84%
You didn't get
enough information.

00:13:24.740 --> 00:13:26.240 align:middle line:90%
You didn't respond to feedback.

00:13:26.240 --> 00:13:28.225 align:middle line:84%
You got defensive when
people gave it to you.

00:13:28.225 --> 00:13:31.430 align:middle line:84%
You picked a bad location,
and nobody came, and then

00:13:31.430 --> 00:13:32.060 align:middle line:90%
you wonder why?

00:13:32.060 --> 00:13:33.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, you picked
the bad location

00:13:33.300 --> 00:13:34.810 align:middle line:84%
because it was
inexpensive instead

00:13:34.810 --> 00:13:37.580 align:middle line:84%
of studying more,
getting more capital,

00:13:37.580 --> 00:13:39.301 align:middle line:90%
before you opened your store.

00:13:39.301 --> 00:13:40.300 align:middle line:90%
There's a lot of things.

00:13:40.300 --> 00:13:41.574 align:middle line:90%
And people blame the economy.

00:13:41.574 --> 00:13:43.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, we know people
during the last recession

00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:46.064 align:middle line:84%
who got really wealthy, so it
couldn't have been the economy.

00:13:46.064 --> 00:13:47.730 align:middle line:84%
We know people that
never get sick so it

00:13:47.730 --> 00:13:50.310 align:middle line:90%
can't be the toxins in the air.

00:13:50.310 --> 00:13:53.540 align:middle line:84%
So what is it that we have
to take responsibility?

00:13:53.540 --> 00:13:56.520 align:middle line:84%
And that's the hardest thing
I get when I do interviews,

00:13:56.520 --> 00:13:59.030 align:middle line:84%
like on the radio
call-ins, well,

00:13:59.030 --> 00:14:00.760 align:middle line:84%
you can't blame
me for my cancer.

00:14:00.760 --> 00:14:01.760 align:middle line:90%
And I go, wait a second.

00:14:01.760 --> 00:14:03.695 align:middle line:90%
Do you only eat organic food?

00:14:03.695 --> 00:14:05.780 align:middle line:84%
Do you wear some
kind of EMF device?

00:14:05.780 --> 00:14:07.240 align:middle line:90%
Which I have on right now.

00:14:07.240 --> 00:14:08.946 align:middle line:90%
Do you drink pure water?

00:14:08.946 --> 00:14:10.820 align:middle line:84%
Are you drinking water
out of plastic bottles

00:14:10.820 --> 00:14:11.990 align:middle line:90%
that have BPA in it?

00:14:11.990 --> 00:14:14.690 align:middle line:84%
Have you detoxed at least
once every two months?

00:14:14.690 --> 00:14:16.860 align:middle line:84%
Do you live next to
a cellphone tower?

00:14:16.860 --> 00:14:18.250 align:middle line:90%
Are you eating GMO?

00:14:18.250 --> 00:14:19.650 align:middle line:90%
You can go down the list.

00:14:19.650 --> 00:14:22.420 align:middle line:84%
Are you keeping
your body alkaline?

00:14:22.420 --> 00:14:24.659 align:middle line:84%
And people go no,
no, no, no, no.

00:14:24.659 --> 00:14:25.700 align:middle line:90%
And then you're a victim?

00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:27.700 align:middle line:90%
Come on.

00:14:27.700 --> 00:14:29.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Taking responsibility.

00:14:29.450 --> 00:14:32.240 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take a look
here at Jack talking about how

00:14:32.240 --> 00:14:32.960 align:middle line:90%
to goal set.

00:14:32.960 --> 00:14:34.270 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:14:34.270 --> 00:14:36.857 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: So why is it
so important to set goals?

00:14:36.857 --> 00:14:38.190 align:middle line:90%
Because you want to be a winner.

00:14:38.190 --> 00:14:40.786 align:middle line:84%
You want to be one of the
people that gets what you want.

00:14:40.786 --> 00:14:43.160 align:middle line:84%
And the first thing that
happens when you set goals is it

00:14:43.160 --> 00:14:46.310 align:middle line:84%
forces you to sit down and
clarify what you really want.

00:14:46.310 --> 00:14:49.520 align:middle line:84%
Most people never take
the time to really sit

00:14:49.520 --> 00:14:52.020 align:middle line:84%
down and intentionally
plan out their life.

00:14:52.020 --> 00:14:54.020 align:middle line:84%
They live a life of
reaction rather than

00:14:54.020 --> 00:14:56.630 align:middle line:84%
a life of creation,
a life of intention.

00:14:56.630 --> 00:14:58.830 align:middle line:84%
And so when you sit down
to think about, well,

00:14:58.830 --> 00:15:01.050 align:middle line:84%
if I'm going to set goals,
what do I set them for,

00:15:01.050 --> 00:15:02.482 align:middle line:84%
what do I set them
about, you have

00:15:02.482 --> 00:15:04.940 align:middle line:84%
to have some sense of what you
want to create in your life.

00:15:04.940 --> 00:15:07.830 align:middle line:84%
What's the ideal life that
I want to live look like?

00:15:07.830 --> 00:15:09.820 align:middle line:84%
What do I want in
terms of relationships?

00:15:09.820 --> 00:15:11.760 align:middle line:84%
What do I want in terms
of health and fitness?

00:15:11.760 --> 00:15:14.210 align:middle line:84%
How much money do I want to
be bringing into my life?

00:15:14.210 --> 00:15:16.880 align:middle line:84%
What impact do I want
to have in the world?

00:15:16.880 --> 00:15:18.860 align:middle line:84%
So we'll be taking
a look at all that.

00:15:18.860 --> 00:15:21.300 align:middle line:84%
But the key thing is to
sit down and take time.

00:15:21.300 --> 00:15:23.950 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to suggest
that once you stop watching

00:15:23.950 --> 00:15:27.480 align:middle line:84%
this video, you set aside at
least a half hour-- better

00:15:27.480 --> 00:15:30.610 align:middle line:84%
an hour-- and sit, and really
start to think about what do I

00:15:30.610 --> 00:15:31.830 align:middle line:90%
want my life to look like?

00:15:31.830 --> 00:15:33.380 align:middle line:90%
What do I want to experience?

00:15:33.380 --> 00:15:34.800 align:middle line:90%
What do I want to do?

00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:37.247 align:middle line:84%
What I want to be, and
what do I want to have?

00:15:37.247 --> 00:15:39.330 align:middle line:84%
And you can look at this
in any time frame at all.

00:15:39.330 --> 00:15:41.530 align:middle line:84%
You can say, well, these
are my lifetime goals,

00:15:41.530 --> 00:15:44.250 align:middle line:84%
like I want to be in the
speaker's hall of fame,

00:15:44.250 --> 00:15:46.590 align:middle line:84%
or I want to win an
Olympic gold medal,

00:15:46.590 --> 00:15:49.770 align:middle line:84%
or I want to retire with an
investment fund of $30 million

00:15:49.770 --> 00:15:50.870 align:middle line:90%
in my portfolio.

00:15:50.870 --> 00:15:52.810 align:middle line:90%
Those are long term goals.

00:15:52.810 --> 00:15:54.660 align:middle line:84%
But you also want to
have short term goals.

00:15:54.660 --> 00:15:56.743 align:middle line:84%
What you want to accomplish
in the next five years

00:15:56.743 --> 00:15:57.960 align:middle line:90%
and in the next year?

00:15:57.960 --> 00:16:00.580 align:middle line:84%
And think a lot about what
do I want to accomplish?

00:16:00.580 --> 00:16:03.554 align:middle line:84%
12 months from now, where do
I want to be experiencing?

00:16:03.554 --> 00:16:05.470 align:middle line:84%
If we were sitting here
a year from now saying

00:16:05.470 --> 00:16:07.310 align:middle line:84%
what would have to
have happened for you

00:16:07.310 --> 00:16:10.470 align:middle line:84%
to feel really proud and
successful and pleased

00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:12.700 align:middle line:84%
with the success you've
made in that year.

00:16:12.700 --> 00:16:14.830 align:middle line:84%
So we can look at all those
different time frames,

00:16:14.830 --> 00:16:18.710 align:middle line:84%
but sit down and ask yourself,
what do I want to experience?

00:16:18.710 --> 00:16:22.370 align:middle line:84%
And one the things that I teach
people that's really powerful

00:16:22.370 --> 00:16:25.500 align:middle line:84%
is that you can really
look at all different areas

00:16:25.500 --> 00:16:27.610 align:middle line:84%
of your life, and we're
going to jump into that

00:16:27.610 --> 00:16:28.870 align:middle line:90%
in just a few minutes.

00:16:28.870 --> 00:16:31.330 align:middle line:84%
The other thing that's
very valuable about goals

00:16:31.330 --> 00:16:34.310 align:middle line:84%
is they give you a sense
of potential, momentum,

00:16:34.310 --> 00:16:35.360 align:middle line:90%
motivation.

00:16:35.360 --> 00:16:37.360 align:middle line:84%
They give you a sense of
direction in your life.

00:16:37.360 --> 00:16:40.020 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people don't
really have any direction.

00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:42.190 align:middle line:84%
They're just responding
to what other people want,

00:16:42.190 --> 00:16:45.250 align:middle line:84%
the demands they place
on them, and I always

00:16:45.250 --> 00:16:46.800 align:middle line:84%
say that people that
don't have goals

00:16:46.800 --> 00:16:48.237 align:middle line:90%
get used by people who do.

00:16:48.237 --> 00:16:50.320 align:middle line:84%
People that don't have
goals work for other people

00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:51.220 align:middle line:90%
that have them.

00:16:51.220 --> 00:16:53.620 align:middle line:84%
And my friend Jim Brown
once said something

00:16:53.620 --> 00:16:56.499 align:middle line:84%
like, he said, "If
you don't have goals,

00:16:56.499 --> 00:16:58.540 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be part
of other people's goals."

00:16:58.540 --> 00:17:00.248 align:middle line:84%
And I can tell you
what they have in mind

00:17:00.248 --> 00:17:01.170 align:middle line:90%
for you is not much.

00:17:01.170 --> 00:17:03.440 align:middle line:84%
So you want to be someone that's
saying, here's what I want,

00:17:03.440 --> 00:17:05.215 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to go for it,
and created it, and have it

00:17:05.215 --> 00:17:05.970 align:middle line:90%
in my life.

00:17:05.970 --> 00:17:07.990 align:middle line:84%
Another reason that
setting goals is important,

00:17:07.990 --> 00:17:10.140 align:middle line:84%
and I think it's really
the most important reason,

00:17:10.140 --> 00:17:13.140 align:middle line:84%
is that when you set
a goal, it requires

00:17:13.140 --> 00:17:15.500 align:middle line:84%
you to become something
bigger than you already

00:17:15.500 --> 00:17:17.050 align:middle line:90%
are in order to achieve it.

00:17:17.050 --> 00:17:18.950 align:middle line:90%
It requires you to grow.

00:17:18.950 --> 00:17:23.109 align:middle line:84%
My mentor, W. Clement Stone, who
I worked for back in the 1970s,

00:17:23.109 --> 00:17:24.990 align:middle line:84%
he said, "I want
you to set a goal

00:17:24.990 --> 00:17:27.710 align:middle line:84%
so big that it requires
you to stretch and become

00:17:27.710 --> 00:17:29.410 align:middle line:90%
someone worth becoming."

00:17:29.410 --> 00:17:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And the point of that is
that it's not the goal,

00:17:31.460 --> 00:17:33.640 align:middle line:84%
because any goal you
achieve, whether it's

00:17:33.640 --> 00:17:37.085 align:middle line:84%
the car, a house, your TV
show, a great reputation,

00:17:37.085 --> 00:17:41.280 align:middle line:84%
a big portfolio, lots of money,
all that can be taken away.

00:17:41.280 --> 00:17:43.770 align:middle line:84%
Cars are stolen,
houses burn down,

00:17:43.770 --> 00:17:48.080 align:middle line:84%
earthquakes happen, Marriages
dissolve, fortunes are lost,

00:17:48.080 --> 00:17:51.500 align:middle line:84%
but who you became in the
process of developing that can

00:17:51.500 --> 00:17:53.232 align:middle line:90%
never be taken away from you.

00:17:53.232 --> 00:17:54.440 align:middle line:90%
And that's really the payoff.

00:17:54.440 --> 00:17:57.000 align:middle line:84%
It's called mastery
in life, and you

00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.000 align:middle line:84%
want to be putting
yourself out there

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:01.430 align:middle line:84%
and forcing yourself
to grow, to develop

00:18:01.430 --> 00:18:05.860 align:middle line:84%
new skills, new mindsets,
new relationships,

00:18:05.860 --> 00:18:07.590 align:middle line:90%
new competencies, et cetera.

00:18:07.590 --> 00:18:09.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's really
the ultimate outcome

00:18:09.670 --> 00:18:12.175 align:middle line:84%
because that will
always stay with you.

00:18:12.175 --> 00:18:13.580 align:middle line:90%
You can never learn less.

00:18:13.580 --> 00:18:16.410 align:middle line:84%
You can only learn more, and
we want to have you constantly

00:18:16.410 --> 00:18:19.340 align:middle line:84%
growing yourself, and goals
require you to do that.

00:18:19.340 --> 00:18:21.170 align:middle line:84%
And I want you, when
you set your goals,

00:18:21.170 --> 00:18:24.054 align:middle line:84%
to set goals that will
stretch you, not freeze you.

00:18:24.054 --> 00:18:25.470 align:middle line:84%
If they're too
big, you'll freeze.

00:18:25.470 --> 00:18:26.800 align:middle line:84%
It they're too small,
they're boring.

00:18:26.800 --> 00:18:29.370 align:middle line:84%
And if they're just at the right
level, you're going to grow.

00:18:29.370 --> 00:18:32.340 align:middle line:84%
How do you decide what to
write down as your goals?

00:18:32.340 --> 00:18:34.340 align:middle line:84%
We know they need to be
measurable and specific,

00:18:34.340 --> 00:18:36.850 align:middle line:90%
but what do I write down?

00:18:36.850 --> 00:18:39.520 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to suggest three
quick techniques you can do.

00:18:39.520 --> 00:18:42.390 align:middle line:84%
One is what we call an
irritation toleration list.

00:18:42.390 --> 00:18:45.180 align:middle line:84%
You walk through your house or
your apartment, your office,

00:18:45.180 --> 00:18:47.580 align:middle line:84%
your car, your garage,
your factory, anything

00:18:47.580 --> 00:18:51.270 align:middle line:84%
that you have dominion over,
and make a list of everything

00:18:51.270 --> 00:18:53.410 align:middle line:84%
that isn't exactly the
way you want it to be.

00:18:53.410 --> 00:18:55.290 align:middle line:84%
That door never closes
right, I can never

00:18:55.290 --> 00:18:57.190 align:middle line:84%
find a stapler when
I want it, I've

00:18:57.190 --> 00:18:59.830 align:middle line:84%
got this hole in
the screen door,

00:18:59.830 --> 00:19:03.180 align:middle line:84%
I don't have the pots I
need in my kitchen, whatever

00:19:03.180 --> 00:19:05.322 align:middle line:90%
it might be, and make a list.

00:19:05.322 --> 00:19:07.030 align:middle line:84%
And then what I'm
going to suggest you do

00:19:07.030 --> 00:19:09.210 align:middle line:90%
is that's what you don't want.

00:19:09.210 --> 00:19:11.125 align:middle line:90%
Ask yourself what do I want?

00:19:11.125 --> 00:19:13.250 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of times what
people focus on is what

00:19:13.250 --> 00:19:13.840 align:middle line:90%
they don't want.

00:19:13.840 --> 00:19:15.173 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to be a bad parent.

00:19:15.173 --> 00:19:17.320 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to have
my house foreclosed on.

00:19:17.320 --> 00:19:18.970 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to lose my car.

00:19:18.970 --> 00:19:20.981 align:middle line:84%
And now you're focusing
on the very thing

00:19:20.981 --> 00:19:23.230 align:middle line:84%
you don't want is where
you're putting your attention.

00:19:23.230 --> 00:19:24.646 align:middle line:84%
We know from the
law of attraction

00:19:24.646 --> 00:19:27.050 align:middle line:84%
that will actually get you
more of what you don't want.

00:19:27.050 --> 00:19:30.170 align:middle line:84%
So it's OK look at what
you don't want only long

00:19:30.170 --> 00:19:32.470 align:middle line:84%
enough to say, OK, I want
the opposite of that.

00:19:32.470 --> 00:19:34.180 align:middle line:84%
Now that what you
know what you want,

00:19:34.180 --> 00:19:35.680 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to suggest
that a good way

00:19:35.680 --> 00:19:38.410 align:middle line:84%
to get started on that
is to take a weekend

00:19:38.410 --> 00:19:41.130 align:middle line:84%
and just really blitz through
all those things and get them

00:19:41.130 --> 00:19:41.950 align:middle line:90%
handled.

00:19:41.950 --> 00:19:43.800 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people when they
come and they listen to me

00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:45.466 align:middle line:84%
talk like this, they
say, wait a second,

00:19:45.466 --> 00:19:46.750 align:middle line:90%
I want to be a millionaire.

00:19:46.750 --> 00:19:48.130 align:middle line:90%
I want to have world peace.

00:19:48.130 --> 00:19:50.447 align:middle line:84%
I want to end hunger in
Pakistan, whatever it is,

00:19:50.447 --> 00:19:52.030 align:middle line:84%
and you want to walk
through and worry

00:19:52.030 --> 00:19:54.500 align:middle line:84%
about I don't have a stapler
next to the Xerox machine?

00:19:54.500 --> 00:19:56.400 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is
yes, and here's why.

00:19:56.400 --> 00:19:58.740 align:middle line:84%
If you are sitting there
going, I can't even

00:19:58.740 --> 00:20:00.999 align:middle line:84%
get the door to close
on my garage, what

00:20:00.999 --> 00:20:03.290 align:middle line:84%
makes me think I could create
peace in the Middle East?

00:20:03.290 --> 00:20:05.689 align:middle line:84%
And so basically you've got
to start having successes

00:20:05.689 --> 00:20:07.730 align:middle line:84%
with a lot of these little
things getting handled

00:20:07.730 --> 00:20:09.680 align:middle line:84%
in your life so it
gives you the confidence

00:20:09.680 --> 00:20:11.370 align:middle line:84%
that you can handle
the big things.

00:20:11.370 --> 00:20:14.480 align:middle line:84%
Secondly, it clears the
slate so that every time you

00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:16.730 align:middle line:84%
walk past a Xerox
machine, you're not going,

00:20:16.730 --> 00:20:18.020 align:middle line:90%
man, I wish we had a stapler.

00:20:18.020 --> 00:20:20.010 align:middle line:84%
I can't find this,
I can't find that.

00:20:20.010 --> 00:20:22.340 align:middle line:84%
It allows you to really
start focusing on the bigger

00:20:22.340 --> 00:20:23.174 align:middle line:90%
things in your life.

00:20:23.174 --> 00:20:24.840 align:middle line:84%
So that's the first
way to start getting

00:20:24.840 --> 00:20:26.250 align:middle line:84%
clear about some
things you want.

00:20:26.250 --> 00:20:30.190 align:middle line:84%
Secondly, I'm going to suggest
you make a list of 101 goals

00:20:30.190 --> 00:20:32.780 align:middle line:84%
that you want to
achieve before you die.

00:20:32.780 --> 00:20:33.364 align:middle line:90%
101 goal list.

00:20:33.364 --> 00:20:35.280 align:middle line:84%
You may have seen the
movie "The Bucket List?"

00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:36.410 align:middle line:90%
It's the same thing.

00:20:36.410 --> 00:20:38.610 align:middle line:84%
There's Morgan Freeman
and Jack Nicholson saying,

00:20:38.610 --> 00:20:39.880 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to die soon,
there's all these things

00:20:39.880 --> 00:20:41.010 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to do.

00:20:41.010 --> 00:20:43.540 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to get to the
end of your life and all these,

00:20:43.540 --> 00:20:46.454 align:middle line:84%
well, someday I wish I had,
and not have done them.

00:20:46.454 --> 00:20:48.620 align:middle line:84%
John Goddard, who I write
about in my first "Chicken

00:20:48.620 --> 00:20:50.930 align:middle line:84%
Soup For The Soul"
book, at the age of 15

00:20:50.930 --> 00:20:54.410 align:middle line:84%
made a list of 126 goals
that he wanted to achieve.

00:20:54.410 --> 00:20:55.960 align:middle line:84%
And when I met him
he was in the 70s.

00:20:55.960 --> 00:20:58.680 align:middle line:84%
He'd achieved 117
of those goals.

00:20:58.680 --> 00:21:01.430 align:middle line:84%
He'd been to the
Great Wall of China,

00:21:01.430 --> 00:21:03.580 align:middle line:84%
gone to the Great
Pyramids, he'd gone down

00:21:03.580 --> 00:21:05.470 align:middle line:84%
the Nile River in
a boat, and he'd

00:21:05.470 --> 00:21:07.740 align:middle line:84%
done about everything anyone
could ever think to do.

00:21:07.740 --> 00:21:11.050 align:middle line:84%
But because he sets that list
and every year he reviewed it,

00:21:11.050 --> 00:21:12.980 align:middle line:84%
and said, OK, what do
I want to do this year,

00:21:12.980 --> 00:21:14.575 align:middle line:90%
he led a magical life.

00:21:14.575 --> 00:21:17.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So let's talk about,
if we can, some of your goals,

00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:20.730 align:middle line:84%
if you can, in this new,
not phase in your life,

00:21:20.730 --> 00:21:23.380 align:middle line:90%
but evolution of your life.

00:21:23.380 --> 00:21:25.550 align:middle line:90%
What are some of your new goals?

00:21:25.550 --> 00:21:28.050 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Well, we kind of
touched on a little bit of that

00:21:28.050 --> 00:21:30.355 align:middle line:84%
before, to have a
million trainers by 2030.

00:21:30.355 --> 00:21:32.474 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:21:32.474 --> 00:21:34.890 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: This book's coming
out in its 10th anniversary

00:21:34.890 --> 00:21:35.389 align:middle line:90%
edition.

00:21:35.389 --> 00:21:38.470 align:middle line:84%
I want to see 500,000
copies sold this year.

00:21:38.470 --> 00:21:40.370 align:middle line:84%
I have a new book
coming out later

00:21:40.370 --> 00:21:42.335 align:middle line:84%
this year called "The
30-Day Sobriety Solution,

00:21:42.335 --> 00:21:44.650 align:middle line:84%
How To Get Sober Or Cut
Back Drinking In The Privacy

00:21:44.650 --> 00:21:45.590 align:middle line:90%
Of Your Own Home."

00:21:45.590 --> 00:21:47.730 align:middle line:84%
I want to see
300,000 of those get

00:21:47.730 --> 00:21:48.900 align:middle line:90%
sold by the end of the year.

00:21:48.900 --> 00:21:49.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:21:49.600 --> 00:21:51.600 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: And that's
a really good book.

00:21:51.600 --> 00:21:54.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm working with a guy
who's got an 85% success

00:21:54.220 --> 00:21:57.630 align:middle line:84%
rate in his coaching program
using most of my principles,

00:21:57.630 --> 00:21:59.940 align:middle line:84%
and some other things like
NLP and things like that.

00:21:59.940 --> 00:22:00.835 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Why did you
write that book?

00:22:00.835 --> 00:22:01.785 align:middle line:90%
Just real quick.

00:22:01.785 --> 00:22:04.120 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Well, I
met him at a retreat

00:22:04.120 --> 00:22:06.130 align:middle line:84%
here in Maui where
we're filming this.

00:22:06.130 --> 00:22:07.940 align:middle line:84%
He came to my
retreat, and I learned

00:22:07.940 --> 00:22:10.410 align:middle line:84%
he was using a lot of my
principles in his program

00:22:10.410 --> 00:22:14.347 align:middle line:84%
and getting great success, but
he had a somewhat small impact

00:22:14.347 --> 00:22:15.180 align:middle line:90%
in the world so far.

00:22:15.180 --> 00:22:17.550 align:middle line:84%
I said we got to get
this out to more people.

00:22:17.550 --> 00:22:19.760 align:middle line:84%
And with your
knowledgeable being

00:22:19.760 --> 00:22:22.080 align:middle line:84%
in that sobriety world--
and I've had several family

00:22:22.080 --> 00:22:24.255 align:middle line:84%
members who are alcoholics
who are also sober now,

00:22:24.255 --> 00:22:27.949 align:middle line:84%
fortunately-- and my
reputation and ability

00:22:27.949 --> 00:22:29.990 align:middle line:84%
to get books on in the
world, it would be a shame

00:22:29.990 --> 00:22:31.320 align:middle line:90%
not to do this.

00:22:31.320 --> 00:22:33.810 align:middle line:90%
And so we decided to do it.

00:22:33.810 --> 00:22:36.690 align:middle line:84%
And it was a very
beautiful process

00:22:36.690 --> 00:22:38.110 align:middle line:90%
of putting this together.

00:22:38.110 --> 00:22:41.340 align:middle line:84%
We actually beta tested the book
along with the website and all

00:22:41.340 --> 00:22:43.370 align:middle line:84%
the coaching he was
doing, and everyone

00:22:43.370 --> 00:22:44.780 align:middle line:90%
had major breakthroughs.

00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:47.307 align:middle line:84%
Because, see, what
happened, he was in AA,

00:22:47.307 --> 00:22:50.030 align:middle line:84%
and AA's a great
thing, but they only

00:22:50.030 --> 00:22:51.749 align:middle line:90%
have about a 20% success rate.

00:22:51.749 --> 00:22:52.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, really?

00:22:52.540 --> 00:22:53.248 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Yeah.

00:22:53.248 --> 00:22:56.060 align:middle line:84%
People that go and stay,
great, but most people go,

00:22:56.060 --> 00:22:57.250 align:middle line:90%
they don't stay.

00:22:57.250 --> 00:22:58.780 align:middle line:90%
There's something missing there.

00:22:58.780 --> 00:23:01.162 align:middle line:84%
I've been to several AA
meetings with my kids,

00:23:01.162 --> 00:23:02.620 align:middle line:84%
and I'm always
sitting there going,

00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:04.078 align:middle line:84%
God, I want to run
an exercise now.

00:23:04.078 --> 00:23:05.755 align:middle line:84%
God, I'd love to
lead a meditation.

00:23:05.755 --> 00:23:07.830 align:middle line:84%
Well, if they can only deal with
that, that would solve that.

00:23:07.830 --> 00:23:08.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What's missing.

00:23:08.740 --> 00:23:10.156 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Go to
the core of what

00:23:10.156 --> 00:23:12.100 align:middle line:84%
got them in there in the
first place, which is

00:23:12.100 --> 00:23:13.700 align:middle line:90%
there weren't alcohol deprived.

00:23:13.700 --> 00:23:16.060 align:middle line:84%
They were, like, needing to
self-medicate their pain,

00:23:16.060 --> 00:23:18.850 align:middle line:84%
or they were afraid they
didn't have a purpose in life.

00:23:18.850 --> 00:23:23.350 align:middle line:84%
So he was going to AA
meetings, relapsed three times,

00:23:23.350 --> 00:23:25.350 align:middle line:84%
listened to a Tony
Robbins tape, said,

00:23:25.350 --> 00:23:28.070 align:middle line:84%
why aren't they teaching
this stuff in rehab

00:23:28.070 --> 00:23:31.250 align:middle line:90%
and in the recovery programs?

00:23:31.250 --> 00:23:32.750 align:middle line:84%
So he started putting
that together,

00:23:32.750 --> 00:23:35.050 align:middle line:84%
ran across my book, started
applying a lot of that.

00:23:35.050 --> 00:23:36.540 align:middle line:90%
So that's how it came together.

00:23:36.540 --> 00:23:39.260 align:middle line:84%
And really now what we have is
the best of that whole recovery

00:23:39.260 --> 00:23:41.880 align:middle line:84%
world mixing together with the
best of the human potential

00:23:41.880 --> 00:23:44.460 align:middle line:84%
and consciousness and
transformation movement,

00:23:44.460 --> 00:23:46.280 align:middle line:84%
which has always
needed to happen.

00:23:46.280 --> 00:23:48.390 align:middle line:90%
And so now we get to do that.

00:23:48.390 --> 00:23:50.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Speaking
of transformation,

00:23:50.930 --> 00:23:53.010 align:middle line:84%
you have created the
Transformational Leadership

00:23:53.010 --> 00:23:56.620 align:middle line:84%
Council, which is such a
heart-centered, beautiful

00:23:56.620 --> 00:23:59.270 align:middle line:84%
environment to be in,
and you've created

00:23:59.270 --> 00:24:02.630 align:middle line:84%
a field of amazing
leaders and people

00:24:02.630 --> 00:24:05.670 align:middle line:90%
who lead movements in one space.

00:24:05.670 --> 00:24:10.750 align:middle line:84%
Have you always been this much
of a heart-centered person?

00:24:10.750 --> 00:24:13.770 align:middle line:84%
I know that we've talked before
in an interview about a very

00:24:13.770 --> 00:24:15.710 align:middle line:84%
rocky childhood that
you had, growing up

00:24:15.710 --> 00:24:17.830 align:middle line:84%
on different sides
of the tracks,

00:24:17.830 --> 00:24:23.310 align:middle line:84%
and had to go through a lot of
learning at the very beginning.

00:24:23.310 --> 00:24:25.190 align:middle line:84%
Have you get evolved
in that way now

00:24:25.190 --> 00:24:29.556 align:middle line:84%
to the ultimate of your lessons
just being about love, Jack?

00:24:29.556 --> 00:24:32.340 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Well,
the reality is that I

00:24:32.340 --> 00:24:36.160 align:middle line:84%
was a very cynical, shy,
somewhat judgmental person

00:24:36.160 --> 00:24:39.954 align:middle line:84%
growing up, and I picked up from
my parents the way they lived.

00:24:39.954 --> 00:24:41.120 align:middle line:90%
And they hated big business.

00:24:41.120 --> 00:24:42.835 align:middle line:90%
They hated corporations.

00:24:42.835 --> 00:24:44.897 align:middle line:84%
So I became a
hippie in the '60s,

00:24:44.897 --> 00:24:46.230 align:middle line:90%
and I hated all that stuff, too.

00:24:46.230 --> 00:24:49.124 align:middle line:84%
Very counter cultural, so
a lot of against energy.

00:24:49.124 --> 00:24:51.290 align:middle line:84%
And I think a lot of the
things I was against needed

00:24:51.290 --> 00:24:52.900 align:middle line:84%
transformation, but
being against them

00:24:52.900 --> 00:24:54.070 align:middle line:90%
wasn't going to change it.

00:24:54.070 --> 00:24:56.640 align:middle line:84%
You need to come from love,
and understanding, compassion,

00:24:56.640 --> 00:24:58.420 align:middle line:90%
and then you can embrace.

00:24:58.420 --> 00:25:01.410 align:middle line:84%
So it was a lot of
years of psychotherapy,

00:25:01.410 --> 00:25:07.820 align:middle line:84%
meditation, Byron Katie's
work, Sedona Method work, EFT.

00:25:07.820 --> 00:25:11.530 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I have probably done
everything from Arika to Zen,

00:25:11.530 --> 00:25:15.450 align:middle line:90%
A to Z.

00:25:15.450 --> 00:25:16.960 align:middle line:90%
Which has been great.

00:25:16.960 --> 00:25:18.990 align:middle line:84%
It's like I'm still
growing, I'm still loving.

00:25:18.990 --> 00:25:20.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm learning to love.

00:25:20.730 --> 00:25:23.480 align:middle line:84%
I once said my autobiography,
if I ever write it,

00:25:23.480 --> 00:25:27.266 align:middle line:84%
is going to be called "Loving
To Learn, Learning To Love."

00:25:27.266 --> 00:25:29.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's why I
brought it up, yes.

00:25:29.330 --> 00:25:33.040 align:middle line:84%
I know you as a very
loving human being.

00:25:33.040 --> 00:25:36.060 align:middle line:84%
I watch you in the
exercises that your lead,

00:25:36.060 --> 00:25:37.650 align:middle line:90%
and they're so heart-centered.

00:25:37.650 --> 00:25:40.250 align:middle line:84%
I see the joy that
comes out of your eyes

00:25:40.250 --> 00:25:43.690 align:middle line:84%
when you see that type of
love connection in the room,

00:25:43.690 --> 00:25:47.780 align:middle line:84%
and it just inspires me to see
what a heart-centered person

00:25:47.780 --> 00:25:48.690 align:middle line:90%
that you are.

00:25:48.690 --> 00:25:50.800 align:middle line:84%
And so I was wondering
how that comes

00:25:50.800 --> 00:25:53.150 align:middle line:84%
into play with what it is
that you do around goal

00:25:53.150 --> 00:25:55.074 align:middle line:90%
setting, around your actions.

00:25:55.074 --> 00:25:56.990 align:middle line:84%
Your next steps, what
you set up for yourself.

00:25:56.990 --> 00:25:59.430 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Well, there's a
very important distinction

00:25:59.430 --> 00:26:00.890 align:middle line:90%
that I'll share with you.

00:26:00.890 --> 00:26:02.580 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you've ever
interviewed Michael Beckwith

00:26:02.580 --> 00:26:04.996 align:middle line:84%
and if he's shared his four
steps of spiritual development

00:26:04.996 --> 00:26:07.580 align:middle line:84%
with you, but this was
really revelatory to me

00:26:07.580 --> 00:26:10.240 align:middle line:90%
because I do teach goal setting.

00:26:10.240 --> 00:26:12.660 align:middle line:84%
Michael said there's four
stages of spiritual development.

00:26:12.660 --> 00:26:13.743 align:middle line:90%
The first stage is victim.

00:26:13.743 --> 00:26:15.010 align:middle line:90%
God's doing it to me.

00:26:15.010 --> 00:26:15.690 align:middle line:90%
I'm a victim.

00:26:15.690 --> 00:26:16.810 align:middle line:90%
God, what did I do?

00:26:16.810 --> 00:26:17.726 align:middle line:90%
Why do I deserve this?

00:26:17.726 --> 00:26:18.300 align:middle line:90%
Et cetera.

00:26:18.300 --> 00:26:22.170 align:middle line:84%
The second stage is where
you realize that you can

00:26:22.170 --> 00:26:24.530 align:middle line:90%
work with God's universal laws.

00:26:24.530 --> 00:26:26.760 align:middle line:84%
So you learn things like
affirmations, goal setting,

00:26:26.760 --> 00:26:29.050 align:middle line:84%
visualization,
positive thinking,

00:26:29.050 --> 00:26:32.090 align:middle line:84%
how to meditate and intend
and all that, and it works.

00:26:32.090 --> 00:26:33.090 align:middle line:90%
And so you say, whoa.

00:26:33.090 --> 00:26:35.180 align:middle line:84%
Now a lot of people
get stuck there.

00:26:35.180 --> 00:26:37.400 align:middle line:84%
There's another level,
which is to say, oh, my God,

00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:38.970 align:middle line:84%
if there's universal
laws, there must

00:26:38.970 --> 00:26:41.080 align:middle line:90%
be something behind those laws.

00:26:41.080 --> 00:26:42.980 align:middle line:90%
I want to find out what that is.

00:26:42.980 --> 00:26:47.270 align:middle line:84%
And now instead of
working with God's laws,

00:26:47.270 --> 00:26:49.010 align:middle line:84%
you realize, hey,
wait a second, I

00:26:49.010 --> 00:26:52.130 align:middle line:84%
want to be a channel for that
thing that's creating all this.

00:26:52.130 --> 00:26:54.580 align:middle line:84%
So now you stop saying my
will, and so you say, well,

00:26:54.580 --> 00:26:55.950 align:middle line:90%
what is thy will?

00:26:55.950 --> 00:26:57.110 align:middle line:90%
I will do that.

00:26:57.110 --> 00:26:59.400 align:middle line:84%
So now you're tuning
in for guidance.

00:26:59.400 --> 00:27:00.610 align:middle line:90%
Internal guidance.

00:27:00.610 --> 00:27:03.030 align:middle line:84%
And I had always been
teaching goal setting should

00:27:03.030 --> 00:27:06.430 align:middle line:84%
come from tuning inside,
going to your higher self,

00:27:06.430 --> 00:27:08.180 align:middle line:84%
saying what is it
I'm here to do?

00:27:08.180 --> 00:27:09.270 align:middle line:90%
What is my next step?

00:27:09.270 --> 00:27:10.700 align:middle line:90%
What am I to manifest?

00:27:10.700 --> 00:27:13.350 align:middle line:84%
Then you use the steps of
goal setting and affirmation.

00:27:13.350 --> 00:27:14.250 align:middle line:90%
There's a relation.

00:27:14.250 --> 00:27:16.250 align:middle line:84%
Because now it's not
coming from your ego.

00:27:16.250 --> 00:27:17.964 align:middle line:84%
It's coming from
your higher self.

00:27:17.964 --> 00:27:19.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's not coming
from your bottom line,

00:27:19.880 --> 00:27:21.590 align:middle line:90%
your financial bottom line.

00:27:21.590 --> 00:27:23.524 align:middle line:84%
It's coming from a
totally different source.

00:27:23.524 --> 00:27:24.190 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Yes.

00:27:24.190 --> 00:27:27.190 align:middle line:84%
So everything I've done in the
last 30, 40 years of my life

00:27:27.190 --> 00:27:28.360 align:middle line:90%
has been inner guidance.

00:27:28.360 --> 00:27:30.100 align:middle line:84%
I was guided to do "Chicken
Soup For The Soul."

00:27:30.100 --> 00:27:32.260 align:middle line:84%
I was guided to the set up the
Transformational Leadership

00:27:32.260 --> 00:27:32.890 align:middle line:90%
Council.

00:27:32.890 --> 00:27:36.770 align:middle line:84%
I was guided to set up a
training program for trainers.

00:27:36.770 --> 00:27:38.850 align:middle line:84%
I just came back from
Iran two weeks ago,

00:27:38.850 --> 00:27:42.210 align:middle line:84%
and Iran is considered
an enemy of America.

00:27:42.210 --> 00:27:44.680 align:middle line:84%
But when I go over there,
and I've been there twice,

00:27:44.680 --> 00:27:45.940 align:middle line:90%
the people are just like us.

00:27:45.940 --> 00:27:47.520 align:middle line:84%
They feel their
government's hijacked

00:27:47.520 --> 00:27:49.920 align:middle line:84%
them the way our
government's kind of been

00:27:49.920 --> 00:27:52.120 align:middle line:90%
hijacked by certain elements.

00:27:52.120 --> 00:27:53.520 align:middle line:90%
And they love the west.

00:27:53.520 --> 00:27:54.529 align:middle line:90%
They love us.

00:27:54.529 --> 00:27:56.070 align:middle line:84%
And everywhere I
go, I realize people

00:27:56.070 --> 00:27:57.329 align:middle line:90%
want to love and be loved.

00:27:57.329 --> 00:27:58.620 align:middle line:90%
They want to make a difference.

00:27:58.620 --> 00:28:00.110 align:middle line:90%
They want to feel important.

00:28:00.110 --> 00:28:00.990 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:28:00.990 --> 00:28:03.300 align:middle line:84%
And so whether it's in
China, or whether it's

00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:06.200 align:middle line:84%
in Texas, or whether
it's in South Africa,

00:28:06.200 --> 00:28:07.470 align:middle line:90%
we're all the same.

00:28:07.470 --> 00:28:10.400 align:middle line:84%
And so when you get that, it's
pretty easy to love everybody.

00:28:10.400 --> 00:28:12.954 align:middle line:84%
Someone once said-- they
put their hand up like this,

00:28:12.954 --> 00:28:15.370 align:middle line:84%
and said, so which of these
fingers am I going to cut off?

00:28:15.370 --> 00:28:16.750 align:middle line:90%
If that's all you can see.

00:28:16.750 --> 00:28:19.321 align:middle line:84%
And you realize if you go like
this, they're all connected.

00:28:19.321 --> 00:28:21.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's good!

00:28:21.680 --> 00:28:23.810 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: So basically,
if we're harming anyone,

00:28:23.810 --> 00:28:25.250 align:middle line:90%
we're harming ourself.

00:28:25.250 --> 00:28:28.760 align:middle line:84%
And It's easy to say those
words and read them in a book,

00:28:28.760 --> 00:28:31.800 align:middle line:84%
but when you eventually
get it is really true,

00:28:31.800 --> 00:28:33.265 align:middle line:90%
then it's transformative.

00:28:33.265 --> 00:28:34.975 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Then you
don't judge anybody.

00:28:34.975 --> 00:28:37.300 align:middle line:90%
You don't seclude anybody.

00:28:37.300 --> 00:28:40.130 align:middle line:90%
Yes, that's absolutely true.

00:28:40.130 --> 00:28:42.970 align:middle line:84%
So in this new-- not
new evolution, but

00:28:42.970 --> 00:28:46.010 align:middle line:84%
as you have grown to
now talking about love

00:28:46.010 --> 00:28:50.420 align:middle line:84%
and bringing love into goals,
can you tell us your practice,

00:28:50.420 --> 00:28:52.890 align:middle line:84%
your way of getting
these downloads,

00:28:52.890 --> 00:28:53.895 align:middle line:90%
these divine messages?

00:28:53.895 --> 00:28:54.520 align:middle line:90%
What do you do?

00:28:54.520 --> 00:28:56.359 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: I would
lie to say I meditated

00:28:56.359 --> 00:28:58.150 align:middle line:84%
every day, because if
I get up at 4 o'clock

00:28:58.150 --> 00:29:00.630 align:middle line:84%
to catch a plane somewhere,
I probably won't that day,

00:29:00.630 --> 00:29:03.650 align:middle line:84%
but certainly four to five
days a week I will meditate.

00:29:03.650 --> 00:29:05.470 align:middle line:84%
And I go inside, and
I've got three or four

00:29:05.470 --> 00:29:07.094 align:middle line:84%
different meditations
I do, and I never

00:29:07.094 --> 00:29:09.790 align:middle line:84%
know which one I'm going to
do until I start breathing.

00:29:09.790 --> 00:29:12.830 align:middle line:84%
But they all open
me up to receive,

00:29:12.830 --> 00:29:15.310 align:middle line:84%
to just pay attention to
what wants to come through.

00:29:15.310 --> 00:29:17.890 align:middle line:90%
And sometimes I get words.

00:29:17.890 --> 00:29:19.000 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes I get feelings.

00:29:19.000 --> 00:29:20.680 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes I see pictures.

00:29:20.680 --> 00:29:25.530 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes I get nothing, but
then the next day something

00:29:25.530 --> 00:29:28.120 align:middle line:84%
will happen that I feel
attracted to it, which came

00:29:28.120 --> 00:29:30.270 align:middle line:90%
from that being quiet space.

00:29:30.270 --> 00:29:34.470 align:middle line:84%
And so each day, it's
kind like, OK, what now?

00:29:34.470 --> 00:29:36.644 align:middle line:84%
Deepak Chopra has a
wonderful meditation

00:29:36.644 --> 00:29:37.560 align:middle line:90%
he does every morning.

00:29:37.560 --> 00:29:40.010 align:middle line:84%
He says something to
the effect of please

00:29:40.010 --> 00:29:42.460 align:middle line:84%
help me to be of greater
value to more people.

00:29:42.460 --> 00:29:44.320 align:middle line:90%
Whatever that is, I'll do it.

00:29:44.320 --> 00:29:46.570 align:middle line:84%
And so I kind of do that
after I heard he did that.

00:29:46.570 --> 00:29:48.000 align:middle line:90%
I thought that's pretty cool.

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:51.390 align:middle line:84%
And how can I reach more people
and give them more support,

00:29:51.390 --> 00:29:53.590 align:middle line:84%
create less suffering,
more joy, more abundance.

00:29:53.590 --> 00:29:56.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you still have
the monkey mind chatter

00:29:56.480 --> 00:29:59.480 align:middle line:84%
that most of us have when
you start that process?

00:29:59.480 --> 00:30:02.330 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: I would
say yes, but less.

00:30:02.330 --> 00:30:05.000 align:middle line:84%
I've started to
notice-- I'm 70 now,

00:30:05.000 --> 00:30:07.730 align:middle line:84%
and I've been meditating
for a lot of years,

00:30:07.730 --> 00:30:11.980 align:middle line:84%
and there's more quiet
than there used to be.

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:13.360 align:middle line:90%
There really is.

00:30:13.360 --> 00:30:16.970 align:middle line:84%
I had an experience about
two years ago working

00:30:16.970 --> 00:30:20.050 align:middle line:84%
with a shaman, and he said, I'm
going to take you to a place.

00:30:20.050 --> 00:30:23.225 align:middle line:84%
You want to come back, but you
have to promise me you will,

00:30:23.225 --> 00:30:24.850 align:middle line:84%
because if you won't
make that promise,

00:30:24.850 --> 00:30:26.300 align:middle line:90%
I won't take you there.

00:30:26.300 --> 00:30:30.790 align:middle line:84%
And I had an experience
of pure bliss.

00:30:30.790 --> 00:30:32.130 align:middle line:90%
I thought I knew what bliss was.

00:30:32.130 --> 00:30:33.670 align:middle line:90%
We talk about it easily.

00:30:33.670 --> 00:30:35.550 align:middle line:84%
You know, oneness,
no separation.

00:30:35.550 --> 00:30:36.506 align:middle line:90%
There was no observer.

00:30:36.506 --> 00:30:37.880 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing
to be observed.

00:30:37.880 --> 00:30:39.140 align:middle line:90%
It was just oneness.

00:30:39.140 --> 00:30:41.107 align:middle line:84%
And even that
doesn't sound right.

00:30:41.107 --> 00:30:43.190 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when I came
out, my wife was there.

00:30:43.190 --> 00:30:45.850 align:middle line:84%
She said, all you did was cry
for 20 minutes after that,

00:30:45.850 --> 00:30:50.076 align:middle line:84%
and you just kept saying, thank
you, thank you, thank you.

00:30:50.076 --> 00:30:51.280 align:middle line:90%
And I could have died.

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:53.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I really didn't
want to come back,

00:30:53.030 --> 00:30:54.090 align:middle line:90%
but I made the promise.

00:30:54.090 --> 00:30:56.210 align:middle line:84%
My wife was waiting
for me, so I did.

00:30:56.210 --> 00:30:59.880 align:middle line:84%
But from that moment, somehow
there's more quiet in my mind.

00:30:59.880 --> 00:31:02.320 align:middle line:84%
But it's not like I don't
sit in there and go, jeez,

00:31:02.320 --> 00:31:02.960 align:middle line:90%
I got to do so and so.

00:31:02.960 --> 00:31:04.376 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How did
he take you there?

00:31:04.376 --> 00:31:06.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: He took me there
with a substance, actually.

00:31:06.740 --> 00:31:07.672 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:31:07.672 --> 00:31:08.880 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Called ayahuasca.

00:31:08.880 --> 00:31:09.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, ayahuasca.

00:31:09.570 --> 00:31:10.105 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: It's
from the rainforest.

00:31:10.105 --> 00:31:10.667 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:31:10.667 --> 00:31:12.250 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: And I'm
not a big druggie.

00:31:12.250 --> 00:31:13.230 align:middle line:90%
I didn't do it in the '60s.

00:31:13.230 --> 00:31:15.146 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We've talked
about it before on Gaiam.

00:31:15.146 --> 00:31:17.420 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: And I just
decided to do that.

00:31:17.420 --> 00:31:19.400 align:middle line:84%
I've done it once before
in the rainforest,

00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:22.835 align:middle line:90%
and it was profound.

00:31:22.835 --> 00:31:25.335 align:middle line:84%
I mean, literally I'm not the
same person I was before that.

00:31:25.335 --> 00:31:27.168 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can we talk
about that for a second?

00:31:27.168 --> 00:31:28.740 align:middle line:84%
Because I had a near
death experience

00:31:28.740 --> 00:31:30.470 align:middle line:90%
where I visited that place.

00:31:30.470 --> 00:31:32.725 align:middle line:84%
If it's a state or a
place, I don't know.

00:31:32.725 --> 00:31:35.140 align:middle line:84%
If it's another
dimension, I don't really

00:31:35.140 --> 00:31:36.700 align:middle line:90%
think that matters.

00:31:36.700 --> 00:31:41.760 align:middle line:84%
But I went to that pure,
expanded, vast, no separation

00:31:41.760 --> 00:31:47.510 align:middle line:84%
place of consciousness, and I
seek to find that all the time.

00:31:47.510 --> 00:31:48.926 align:middle line:90%
I think it exists here.

00:31:48.926 --> 00:31:50.300 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Oh,
it does, it does.

00:31:50.300 --> 00:31:52.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Here right now.

00:31:52.210 --> 00:31:55.150 align:middle line:84%
Do we need a near death,
falling off a bike that I did,

00:31:55.150 --> 00:31:57.240 align:middle line:90%
or a substance to get there?

00:31:57.240 --> 00:31:58.640 align:middle line:90%
Why can't we tap in?

00:31:58.640 --> 00:32:00.980 align:middle line:90%
What is that ego or whatever?

00:32:00.980 --> 00:32:01.490 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:32:01.490 --> 00:32:02.823 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Well, it's our mind.

00:32:02.823 --> 00:32:07.680 align:middle line:84%
Our mind basically is
afraid, and our ego's

00:32:07.680 --> 00:32:09.410 align:middle line:84%
afraid of dissolving
into that oneness

00:32:09.410 --> 00:32:11.520 align:middle line:84%
because then it
doesn't exist anymore.

00:32:11.520 --> 00:32:14.340 align:middle line:84%
But it's like a drop of water
in the ocean is the ocean,

00:32:14.340 --> 00:32:18.050 align:middle line:84%
it's just not the whole ocean,
any more than I'm all of God,

00:32:18.050 --> 00:32:19.910 align:middle line:90%
but I am God.

00:32:19.910 --> 00:32:22.270 align:middle line:84%
So if we go back to Michael's
concept for a moment,

00:32:22.270 --> 00:32:24.060 align:middle line:84%
it was like, OK,
God's doing it to me.

00:32:24.060 --> 00:32:26.720 align:middle line:84%
Now I can do it with God,
and I'm going to channel God.

00:32:26.720 --> 00:32:29.300 align:middle line:84%
In the fourth stage of
consciousness, I am God.

00:32:29.300 --> 00:32:30.830 align:middle line:90%
Not all of God.

00:32:30.830 --> 00:32:32.450 align:middle line:90%
It's not an arrogant place.

00:32:32.450 --> 00:32:35.330 align:middle line:84%
It's called, oh,
that's what we all are.

00:32:35.330 --> 00:32:37.990 align:middle line:84%
And when I find
that, then imagine

00:32:37.990 --> 00:32:39.970 align:middle line:90%
what my consciousness is.

00:32:39.970 --> 00:32:43.050 align:middle line:84%
So my experience always has been
that we have these mountaintop

00:32:43.050 --> 00:32:45.730 align:middle line:84%
experiences, like
whether it's a meditation

00:32:45.730 --> 00:32:47.930 align:middle line:84%
or it's through some
kind of psychotropic,

00:32:47.930 --> 00:32:51.040 align:middle line:84%
and then we go, oh,
that's possible.

00:32:51.040 --> 00:32:52.040 align:middle line:90%
That really is there.

00:32:52.040 --> 00:32:54.123 align:middle line:84%
Then we come back, and
there's still bills to pay,

00:32:54.123 --> 00:32:56.540 align:middle line:84%
