All right.

00:37:43.490 --> 00:37:46.970 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take a look
here at Jack talking about what

00:37:46.970 --> 00:37:49.290 align:middle line:84%
to do at the first of the
year, but you could do this

00:37:49.290 --> 00:37:50.770 align:middle line:90%
at any first in your life.

00:37:50.770 --> 00:37:52.040 align:middle line:90%
Take a look

00:37:52.040 --> 00:37:54.270 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Because we
now know from research

00:37:54.270 --> 00:37:57.290 align:middle line:84%
that the simple act
of writing a goal down

00:37:57.290 --> 00:38:00.277 align:middle line:84%
increases your chances
of achieving it by 55%.

00:38:00.277 --> 00:38:02.610 align:middle line:84%
This is research done at the
University of Pennsylvania.

00:38:02.610 --> 00:38:05.760 align:middle line:84%
And we know if you write
it down and you read it

00:38:05.760 --> 00:38:07.500 align:middle line:84%
just a couple times
throughout the year,

00:38:07.500 --> 00:38:10.500 align:middle line:90%
it increases your chances 100%.

00:38:10.500 --> 00:38:12.875 align:middle line:84%
And if you read it every
week and review it,

00:38:12.875 --> 00:38:14.500 align:middle line:84%
we know that it
increases your chances.

00:38:14.500 --> 00:38:16.744 align:middle line:84%
You're getting 200% more
than the regular people.

00:38:16.744 --> 00:38:18.660 align:middle line:84%
That's how many goals
you're going to achieve.

00:38:18.660 --> 00:38:20.680 align:middle line:90%
So writing it down is critical.

00:38:20.680 --> 00:38:22.711 align:middle line:90%
So make that list, and be brave.

00:38:22.711 --> 00:38:23.960 align:middle line:90%
Just put down things you want.

00:38:23.960 --> 00:38:25.793 align:middle line:84%
Don't worry about how
it's going to show up.

00:38:25.793 --> 00:38:27.480 align:middle line:84%
We'll talk about
that a little later.

00:38:27.480 --> 00:38:29.229 align:middle line:84%
And the third thing
I'm going to recommend

00:38:29.229 --> 00:38:31.334 align:middle line:84%
is what we call the
vision exercise,

00:38:31.334 --> 00:38:33.250 align:middle line:84%
to look at your life--
and we divide your life

00:38:33.250 --> 00:38:34.370 align:middle line:90%
into seven areas.

00:38:34.370 --> 00:38:36.010 align:middle line:90%
There's relationships.

00:38:36.010 --> 00:38:37.770 align:middle line:90%
There's finance and money.

00:38:37.770 --> 00:38:39.610 align:middle line:90%
There's your job and career.

00:38:39.610 --> 00:38:41.190 align:middle line:90%
There's health and fitness.

00:38:41.190 --> 00:38:42.950 align:middle line:90%
There's fun and recreation.

00:38:42.950 --> 00:38:45.160 align:middle line:84%
There's what we call
personal, which is just things

00:38:45.160 --> 00:38:47.100 align:middle line:84%
I want to own, things
I want to do just

00:38:47.100 --> 00:38:48.380 align:middle line:90%
for the sake of doing them.

00:38:48.380 --> 00:38:51.900 align:middle line:84%
This includes your spiritual
goals, your emotional goals,

00:38:51.900 --> 00:38:53.140 align:middle line:90%
your educational goals.

00:38:53.140 --> 00:38:54.999 align:middle line:90%
And lastly, contribution.

00:38:54.999 --> 00:38:57.040 align:middle line:84%
What difference do you
want to make in the world?

00:38:57.040 --> 00:38:58.970 align:middle line:84%
What legacy do
you want to leave?

00:38:58.970 --> 00:39:00.970 align:middle line:84%
And if you were to look
at each of those areas

00:39:00.970 --> 00:39:02.880 align:middle line:84%
and say one year from
now what would have

00:39:02.880 --> 00:39:05.840 align:middle line:84%
I liked to have accomplished
in that area of my life,

00:39:05.840 --> 00:39:08.710 align:middle line:84%
and then say, OK, that's a goal
I'm going to set for myself,

00:39:08.710 --> 00:39:10.270 align:middle line:90%
now you've got seven goals.

00:39:10.270 --> 00:39:12.690 align:middle line:84%
Now for some people, seven
goals may be too many.

00:39:12.690 --> 00:39:14.400 align:middle line:84%
You might want to
say, well, that's more

00:39:14.400 --> 00:39:15.530 align:middle line:90%
than I want to take on.

00:39:15.530 --> 00:39:17.910 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I'm going to prioritize
and pick three or four.

00:39:17.910 --> 00:39:18.564 align:middle line:90%
That's fine.

00:39:18.564 --> 00:39:20.230 align:middle line:84%
We don't want you to
overwhelm yourself.

00:39:20.230 --> 00:39:22.450 align:middle line:84%
But if you really
want a balanced life

00:39:22.450 --> 00:39:25.780 align:middle line:84%
and a very fulfilling life in
all areas, so you're healthy,

00:39:25.780 --> 00:39:28.010 align:middle line:84%
you're happy, and
you're successful,

00:39:28.010 --> 00:39:30.475 align:middle line:84%
and you've got a great
energy and your body,

00:39:30.475 --> 00:39:32.100 align:middle line:84%
and you're getting
out there and making

00:39:32.100 --> 00:39:33.641 align:middle line:84%
a difference in the
world, and you're

00:39:33.641 --> 00:39:35.461 align:middle line:84%
growing your financial
world, you're

00:39:35.461 --> 00:39:36.710 align:middle line:90%
going to have a great balance.

00:39:36.710 --> 00:39:39.001 align:middle line:84%
So we want you to look at
all those areas of your life,

00:39:39.001 --> 00:39:41.090 align:middle line:84%
and then think
about specifically

00:39:41.090 --> 00:39:43.174 align:middle line:84%
what's one thing I
want to accomplish

00:39:43.174 --> 00:39:44.340 align:middle line:90%
in every one of those areas.

00:39:44.340 --> 00:39:48.165 align:middle line:84%
And if you do that, you're going
to have a really great year,

00:39:48.165 --> 00:39:50.290 align:middle line:84%
and you'll have a head
start in setting your goals.

00:39:50.290 --> 00:39:52.580 align:middle line:84%
So let's look at some of the
common traps and pitfalls

00:39:52.580 --> 00:39:54.400 align:middle line:84%
that people fall
into that stop them

00:39:54.400 --> 00:39:56.760 align:middle line:84%
from setting goals
correctly and also

00:39:56.760 --> 00:39:58.290 align:middle line:90%
from achieving their goals.

00:39:58.290 --> 00:40:01.630 align:middle line:84%
Number one is what we
call unrealistic goals.

00:40:01.630 --> 00:40:04.520 align:middle line:84%
People say, OK, I want
to do something that's

00:40:04.520 --> 00:40:06.630 align:middle line:84%
totally impossible for
them, but they just

00:40:06.630 --> 00:40:09.332 align:middle line:84%
got it out of someplace like
the cultural norms they see.

00:40:09.332 --> 00:40:10.790 align:middle line:84%
Everyone wants to
be a millionaire.

00:40:10.790 --> 00:40:13.120 align:middle line:84%
So we'll have people
in our seminars

00:40:13.120 --> 00:40:15.089 align:middle line:84%
that are making $35,000
a year, and we'll

00:40:15.089 --> 00:40:17.130 align:middle line:84%
say what's your financial
goal for the next year?

00:40:17.130 --> 00:40:18.421 align:middle line:90%
And they go, a million dollars.

00:40:18.421 --> 00:40:20.360 align:middle line:84%
What about people
making $500,000 a year?

00:40:20.360 --> 00:40:21.068 align:middle line:90%
What's your goal?

00:40:21.068 --> 00:40:22.000 align:middle line:90%
A million dollars.

00:40:22.000 --> 00:40:24.400 align:middle line:84%
And so there's this
external cultural norm

00:40:24.400 --> 00:40:26.060 align:middle line:84%
that says, oh, a
million dollars,

00:40:26.060 --> 00:40:29.690 align:middle line:84%
but it's not really necessarily
relevant to your situation.

00:40:29.690 --> 00:40:31.330 align:middle line:84%
One of the concepts
that we teach

00:40:31.330 --> 00:40:33.017 align:middle line:84%
is that there are
four levels that you

00:40:33.017 --> 00:40:34.100 align:middle line:90%
can be setting goals from.

00:40:34.100 --> 00:40:36.259 align:middle line:84%
The first is called
repair and recovery.

00:40:36.259 --> 00:40:38.300 align:middle line:84%
If you're sitting there,
and you've just come out

00:40:38.300 --> 00:40:40.960 align:middle line:84%
of bankruptcy, or
you've lost your job,

00:40:40.960 --> 00:40:43.260 align:middle line:84%
or you have no foundation
meaning you don't have

00:40:43.260 --> 00:40:45.950 align:middle line:84%
any kind of infrastructure
to start a business with,

00:40:45.950 --> 00:40:50.000 align:middle line:84%
no assets, nothing
you can invest with,

00:40:50.000 --> 00:40:52.790 align:middle line:84%
making a million dollars in
one year, it's not impossible,

00:40:52.790 --> 00:40:53.920 align:middle line:90%
but it's not likely.

00:40:53.920 --> 00:40:56.280 align:middle line:84%
And so you want to say
what would be a next step

00:40:56.280 --> 00:40:58.270 align:middle line:84%
up for me to get me
from repair and recovery

00:40:58.270 --> 00:41:00.120 align:middle line:90%
to what we call foundation?

00:41:00.120 --> 00:41:01.930 align:middle line:84%
I remember when I first
started my company.

00:41:01.930 --> 00:41:03.810 align:middle line:90%
I didn't have a typewriter.

00:41:03.810 --> 00:41:05.910 align:middle line:90%
I had one phone in my house.

00:41:05.910 --> 00:41:08.530 align:middle line:84%
I can remember we had like
literally five splitters

00:41:08.530 --> 00:41:10.754 align:middle line:84%
taking phones off to
five phones a year later

00:41:10.754 --> 00:41:12.795 align:middle line:84%
because we didn't have
enough money at that point

00:41:12.795 --> 00:41:15.300 align:middle line:84%
to even go out and
rent an office space.

00:41:15.300 --> 00:41:17.840 align:middle line:84%
So you have to build
up this infrastructure

00:41:17.840 --> 00:41:19.705 align:middle line:90%
and then create this foundation.

00:41:19.705 --> 00:41:21.080 align:middle line:84%
Are you coming
from a foundation?

00:41:21.080 --> 00:41:22.109 align:middle line:90%
Do you have the basics?

00:41:22.109 --> 00:41:23.150 align:middle line:90%
Do you have an education?

00:41:23.150 --> 00:41:24.770 align:middle line:90%
Do you have the skills you need?

00:41:24.770 --> 00:41:26.230 align:middle line:90%
Do you have the competencies?

00:41:26.230 --> 00:41:29.752 align:middle line:84%
Do you have the relationships,
the network, whatever.

00:41:29.752 --> 00:41:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And then once you have
that, you can move

00:41:31.460 --> 00:41:33.390 align:middle line:90%
into place we call abundance.

00:41:33.390 --> 00:41:35.590 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people don't
have any abundance.

00:41:35.590 --> 00:41:36.920 align:middle line:90%
No abundance of time.

00:41:36.920 --> 00:41:38.030 align:middle line:90%
No abundance of friends.

00:41:38.030 --> 00:41:39.170 align:middle line:90%
No abundance of network.

00:41:39.170 --> 00:41:40.780 align:middle line:90%
No abundance of opportunities.

00:41:40.780 --> 00:41:43.256 align:middle line:84%
But in my life, I have
an abundance of all that.

00:41:43.256 --> 00:41:44.630 align:middle line:84%
And eventually
you get to a level

00:41:44.630 --> 00:41:46.004 align:middle line:84%
where you can set
goals from that

00:41:46.004 --> 00:41:48.020 align:middle line:90%
where I can build huge dreams.

00:41:48.020 --> 00:41:51.970 align:middle line:84%
We can set up offices in
25 cities around the world.

00:41:51.970 --> 00:41:54.190 align:middle line:84%
We can invest in all
kinds of programs,

00:41:54.190 --> 00:41:56.730 align:middle line:84%
and projects, and
workshops to develop.

00:41:56.730 --> 00:41:59.230 align:middle line:84%
The last stage is
called mastery.

00:41:59.230 --> 00:42:01.170 align:middle line:84%
We want to get to
mastery, but you

00:42:01.170 --> 00:42:04.712 align:middle line:84%
can't go from repair
and recovery to mastery.

00:42:04.712 --> 00:42:06.170 align:middle line:84%
If you just got
out of the hospital

00:42:06.170 --> 00:42:08.070 align:middle line:84%
and you had cancer
surgery, you're

00:42:08.070 --> 00:42:10.030 align:middle line:84%
not going to be
running a 100 yard

00:42:10.030 --> 00:42:14.240 align:middle line:84%
dash in nine seconds or a
26 mile marathon next month.

00:42:14.240 --> 00:42:17.070 align:middle line:84%
And so your goals
need to be relevant

00:42:17.070 --> 00:42:18.420 align:middle line:90%
based on where you start from.

00:42:18.420 --> 00:42:21.950 align:middle line:84%
So really sit back and
say, OK, is this a goal

00:42:21.950 --> 00:42:23.660 align:middle line:90%
that's believable for me?

00:42:23.660 --> 00:42:25.530 align:middle line:84%
Another thing you
want to look at,

00:42:25.530 --> 00:42:27.870 align:middle line:90%
is this something I really want?

00:42:27.870 --> 00:42:30.240 align:middle line:84%
Because so many of our goals
are created out of shoulds.

00:42:30.240 --> 00:42:31.940 align:middle line:90%
I should lose weight.

00:42:31.940 --> 00:42:33.520 align:middle line:90%
I should exercise more.

00:42:33.520 --> 00:42:35.070 align:middle line:90%
I should eat more healthy.

00:42:35.070 --> 00:42:37.320 align:middle line:84%
I should do this
thing with my family.

00:42:37.320 --> 00:42:39.450 align:middle line:84%
But if it's not
something you want to do,

00:42:39.450 --> 00:42:41.919 align:middle line:84%
it's going to show up year
after year on your goal sheet,

00:42:41.919 --> 00:42:43.960 align:middle line:84%
and it's going to be one
that you never get done.

00:42:43.960 --> 00:42:45.670 align:middle line:90%
And why don't you get it done?

00:42:45.670 --> 00:42:47.959 align:middle line:84%
Because deep down, it doesn't
have any juice for you.

00:42:47.959 --> 00:42:48.750 align:middle line:90%
There's no passion.

00:42:48.750 --> 00:42:50.290 align:middle line:90%
There's no excitement about it.

00:42:50.290 --> 00:42:54.110 align:middle line:84%
The things that really make
you go, wow, I want that!

00:42:54.110 --> 00:42:57.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What we heard there
