00:44:54.269 --> 00:44:55.810 align:middle line:84%
to interview me the
night before when

00:44:55.810 --> 00:44:57.150 align:middle line:90%
I was doing a book signing.

00:44:57.150 --> 00:44:58.160 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of
the interview, I

00:44:58.160 --> 00:45:00.409 align:middle line:84%
said that is one of the best
interviews I've ever had.

00:45:00.409 --> 00:45:02.190 align:middle line:90%
Almost as good as Lisa.

00:45:02.190 --> 00:45:04.697 align:middle line:84%
So I said, how long
you been doing this?

00:45:04.697 --> 00:45:06.530 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh, this
is my first interview.

00:45:06.530 --> 00:45:07.917 align:middle line:90%
I said, get out of here.

00:45:07.917 --> 00:45:09.625 align:middle line:84%
And he'd just been
hired by the newspaper

00:45:09.625 --> 00:45:12.120 align:middle line:84%
to interview successful
people about success,

00:45:12.120 --> 00:45:14.190 align:middle line:90%
and he had just lost his job.

00:45:14.190 --> 00:45:16.990 align:middle line:84%
He'd owned a restaurant that
bankrupted because of fighting

00:45:16.990 --> 00:45:17.980 align:middle line:90%
between the partners.

00:45:17.980 --> 00:45:18.980 align:middle line:90%
His girlfriend left him.

00:45:18.980 --> 00:45:19.936 align:middle line:90%
He was couch surfing.

00:45:19.936 --> 00:45:21.060 align:middle line:90%
He had no money and no car.

00:45:21.060 --> 00:45:22.060 align:middle line:90%
A friend dropped him off.

00:45:22.060 --> 00:45:23.790 align:middle line:84%
I said, John, how much
money do you have?

00:45:23.790 --> 00:45:24.930 align:middle line:90%
He says, $3.80.

00:45:24.930 --> 00:45:26.450 align:middle line:90%
That's my total net worth.

00:45:26.450 --> 00:45:28.677 align:middle line:90%
So I have him $20 to buy dinner.

00:45:28.677 --> 00:45:30.260 align:middle line:84%
I had to buy a book
from the bookstore

00:45:30.260 --> 00:45:32.120 align:middle line:84%
to give it to him because
I didn't have any.

00:45:32.120 --> 00:45:33.550 align:middle line:90%
I'm in Manila, right?

00:45:33.550 --> 00:45:36.390 align:middle line:84%
And so I come back to
Manila two years later

00:45:36.390 --> 00:45:38.110 align:middle line:84%
to do a one-day
seminar, and in walks

00:45:38.110 --> 00:45:42.310 align:middle line:84%
John wearing gold Doc Marten
shoes, beautiful blue blazer,

00:45:42.310 --> 00:45:46.290 align:middle line:84%
and a big logo on in gold on
it, and then 10 guys behind him

00:45:46.290 --> 00:45:48.800 align:middle line:84%
all with polo shirts
with the same logo.

00:45:48.800 --> 00:45:50.890 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you're the
guy that interviewed me.

00:45:50.890 --> 00:45:51.970 align:middle line:90%
You look different.

00:45:51.970 --> 00:45:55.180 align:middle line:84%
He said, I am now the number
one motivational speaker

00:45:55.180 --> 00:45:56.520 align:middle line:90%
in the Philippines.

00:45:56.520 --> 00:45:59.630 align:middle line:84%
I have two cars, a house, a
beach house, a radio show,

00:45:59.630 --> 00:46:00.830 align:middle line:90%
a TV show.

00:46:00.830 --> 00:46:02.349 align:middle line:90%
I am getting a million a year.

00:46:02.349 --> 00:46:02.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What!

00:46:02.890 --> 00:46:05.450 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: I've got audiences
of 600 to 1,000 people.

00:46:05.450 --> 00:46:07.180 align:middle line:90%
I said, John, what the heck?

00:46:07.180 --> 00:46:08.410 align:middle line:90%
How'd you do that?

00:46:08.410 --> 00:46:10.590 align:middle line:90%
He said, you gave me your book.

00:46:10.590 --> 00:46:11.769 align:middle line:90%
You were successful.

00:46:11.769 --> 00:46:13.310 align:middle line:84%
Here you are, millions
of books sold,

00:46:13.310 --> 00:46:16.100 align:middle line:84%
multimillionaire, happy
life, good health, all this.

00:46:16.100 --> 00:46:17.805 align:middle line:84%
And he said, that
guy's successful.

00:46:17.805 --> 00:46:19.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm not I'm going
to do everything

00:46:19.720 --> 00:46:20.940 align:middle line:90%
he says in that book.

