00:47:58.960 --> 00:47:59.770 align:middle line:90%
times.

00:47:59.770 --> 00:48:01.404 align:middle line:84%
It's the number
one DVD in China.

00:48:01.404 --> 00:48:03.070 align:middle line:84%
Just being part of
that would be enough.

00:48:03.070 --> 00:48:03.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:48:03.660 --> 00:48:04.159 align:middle line:90%
Wow!

00:48:04.159 --> 00:48:05.930 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: I mean, who knew?

00:48:05.930 --> 00:48:07.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What next?

00:48:07.050 --> 00:48:07.610 align:middle line:90%
My goodness.

00:48:07.610 --> 00:48:10.830 align:middle line:84%
Well, you do teach people how
to bring about their own dreams

00:48:10.830 --> 00:48:13.300 align:middle line:84%
through publishing their own
books and how to self-publish.

00:48:13.300 --> 00:48:14.960 align:middle line:84%
You have a great
piece on that here.

00:48:14.960 --> 00:48:16.876 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take a
look at this video, Jack

00:48:16.876 --> 00:48:19.080 align:middle line:84%
talking about all of you
self-publishers out there.

00:48:19.080 --> 00:48:20.396 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:48:20.396 --> 00:48:23.955 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:48:23.955 --> 00:48:34.266 align:middle line:90%


00:48:34.266 --> 00:48:38.630 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Here's a person who
just sent me a magazine article

00:48:38.630 --> 00:48:42.560 align:middle line:84%
in the mail today, and she's
reading one of our books

00:48:42.560 --> 00:48:44.840 align:middle line:90%
in the magazine.

00:48:44.840 --> 00:48:47.660 align:middle line:90%
There's the picture of the book.

00:48:47.660 --> 00:48:50.340 align:middle line:90%
It's fun.

00:48:50.340 --> 00:48:51.065 align:middle line:90%
I love my work.

00:48:51.065 --> 00:48:53.570 align:middle line:90%


00:48:53.570 --> 00:48:56.060 align:middle line:84%
You know, everyone has to
start with their first book,

00:48:56.060 --> 00:48:57.641 align:middle line:90%
and it's a challenge.

00:48:57.641 --> 00:48:59.890 align:middle line:84%
I remember when I thought
about writing my first book,

00:48:59.890 --> 00:49:02.450 align:middle line:84%
I thought, oh, my God, it seems
like such a huge thing to do.

00:49:02.450 --> 00:49:05.410 align:middle line:84%
I had just finished being a high
school teacher back in Chicago.

00:49:05.410 --> 00:49:07.551 align:middle line:84%
I was teaching in
an inner city school

00:49:07.551 --> 00:49:09.050 align:middle line:84%
where I realized
my students weren't

00:49:09.050 --> 00:49:10.051 align:middle line:90%
that motivated to learn.

00:49:10.051 --> 00:49:11.675 align:middle line:84%
And I was really
excited about history,

00:49:11.675 --> 00:49:12.930 align:middle line:90%
but they didn't seem to be.

00:49:12.930 --> 00:49:15.580 align:middle line:84%
And at first I thought, well,
maybe I'm not a great teacher.

00:49:15.580 --> 00:49:18.340 align:middle line:84%
And then I began to realize
that they didn't believe

00:49:18.340 --> 00:49:20.670 align:middle line:84%
they could learn, so
I started studying

00:49:20.670 --> 00:49:22.410 align:middle line:90%
this area called self-esteem.

00:49:22.410 --> 00:49:24.800 align:middle line:84%
How do you raise kids'
belief in themselves?

00:49:24.800 --> 00:49:26.320 align:middle line:84%
And I started
taking workshops, I

00:49:26.320 --> 00:49:28.270 align:middle line:84%
read all the books I
could get my hands on,

00:49:28.270 --> 00:49:31.277 align:middle line:84%
but I never found the
book that I wanted to buy.

00:49:31.277 --> 00:49:33.360 align:middle line:84%
And someone once said to
me, one of my professors,

00:49:33.360 --> 00:49:35.609 align:middle line:84%
if you can't find the book
you're looking for, it must

00:49:35.609 --> 00:49:36.960 align:middle line:90%
be you're supposed to write it.

00:49:36.960 --> 00:49:39.350 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought,
well, maybe I am.

00:49:39.350 --> 00:49:42.670 align:middle line:84%
And so I sat down, and I
wrote a book on "100 Ways

00:49:42.670 --> 00:49:45.060 align:middle line:84%
To Enhance Self-esteem
In The Classroom."

00:49:45.060 --> 00:49:49.290 align:middle line:84%
And that book, which
was a book for teachers,

00:49:49.290 --> 00:49:52.200 align:middle line:90%
went on to sell 400,000 copies.

00:49:52.200 --> 00:49:52.990 align:middle line:90%
And?

00:49:52.990 --> 00:49:55.740 align:middle line:84%
Literally just it absolutely
changed my career.

00:49:55.740 --> 00:50:00.340 align:middle line:90%


00:50:00.340 --> 00:50:03.209 align:middle line:84%
I don't think there's anything
simple about writing a book.

00:50:03.209 --> 00:50:04.875 align:middle line:84%
You got to deal with
a lot of obstacles.

00:50:04.875 --> 00:50:06.416 align:middle line:84%
First of all, you're
taking time away

00:50:06.416 --> 00:50:09.370 align:middle line:84%
from your family, your
wife, your children.

00:50:09.370 --> 00:50:11.660 align:middle line:84%
There's the self-doubt
you have to confront.

00:50:11.660 --> 00:50:13.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I can't tell
you how many times I

00:50:13.410 --> 00:50:16.311 align:middle line:84%
sit there going like, does
this really read well?

00:50:16.311 --> 00:50:18.060 align:middle line:84%
Is anyone really going
to care about this?

00:50:18.060 --> 00:50:20.194 align:middle line:90%
Am I wasting my time?

00:50:20.194 --> 00:50:22.110 align:middle line:84%
Often you're taking time
away from your health

00:50:22.110 --> 00:50:23.943 align:middle line:84%
because you're sitting
there for long hours.

00:50:23.943 --> 00:50:25.450 align:middle line:84%
I can remember
many times starting

00:50:25.450 --> 00:50:27.080 align:middle line:84%
to write at 7:00 at night,
and the next thing I knew,

00:50:27.080 --> 00:50:28.120 align:middle line:90%
the birds were singing.

00:50:28.120 --> 00:50:29.440 align:middle line:90%
The sun was coming up.

00:50:29.440 --> 00:50:30.670 align:middle line:90%
But I had such a passion.

00:50:30.670 --> 00:50:32.240 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to get
this message out.

00:50:32.240 --> 00:50:34.790 align:middle line:84%
And I just whatever it
took, I was going to do it.

00:50:34.790 --> 00:50:37.271 align:middle line:90%


00:50:37.271 --> 00:50:38.770 align:middle line:84%
So with "Chicken
Soup For The Soul,"

00:50:38.770 --> 00:50:42.130 align:middle line:84%
which is probably my greatest
achievement in my life,

00:50:42.130 --> 00:50:44.840 align:middle line:84%
that came about very
surreptitiously.

00:50:44.840 --> 00:50:47.350 align:middle line:84%
I was giving talks,
and I was illustrating

00:50:47.350 --> 00:50:49.944 align:middle line:84%
all of my seminars and
my workshops and talks

00:50:49.944 --> 00:50:51.860 align:middle line:84%
with stories, because I
know that stories help

00:50:51.860 --> 00:50:54.990 align:middle line:90%
people to remember the concept.

00:50:54.990 --> 00:50:58.770 align:middle line:84%
And I was telling
stories in my talks.

00:50:58.770 --> 00:51:00.480 align:middle line:84%
I was at Boston coming
home on a plane,

00:51:00.480 --> 00:51:02.532 align:middle line:84%
and someone had just
asked me that they day,

00:51:02.532 --> 00:51:03.990 align:middle line:84%
they said that
story about a puppy.

00:51:03.990 --> 00:51:04.970 align:middle line:90%
Is that in the book anywhere?

00:51:04.970 --> 00:51:06.178 align:middle line:90%
My daughter needs to read it.

00:51:06.178 --> 00:51:08.770 align:middle line:84%
A week earlier, someone said
the story about the Girl Scout.

00:51:08.770 --> 00:51:09.530 align:middle line:90%
Is that in the book anywhere?

00:51:09.530 --> 00:51:11.020 align:middle line:90%
My daughter needs to read it.

00:51:11.020 --> 00:51:13.790 align:middle line:84%
So I started writing down
what are the stories I know?

00:51:13.790 --> 00:51:16.820 align:middle line:84%
And came up with like
71, something like that.

00:51:16.820 --> 00:51:18.934 align:middle line:84%
I thought, wow, there's
enough for a book.

00:51:18.934 --> 00:51:20.350 align:middle line:84%
Once you've written
a book, and it

00:51:20.350 --> 00:51:23.125 align:middle line:84%
could take anywhere from six
months to a year write it,

00:51:23.125 --> 00:51:24.125 align:middle line:90%
then you got to sell it.

00:51:24.125 --> 00:51:25.852 align:middle line:84%
And with "Chicken
Soup For The Soul,"

00:51:25.852 --> 00:51:27.310 align:middle line:84%
that's kind of a
classic story now,

00:51:27.310 --> 00:51:31.400 align:middle line:84%
but we were rejected over
the course of a year and more

00:51:31.400 --> 00:51:33.620 align:middle line:90%
by 144 publishers.

00:51:33.620 --> 00:51:35.590 align:middle line:84%
They said people don't
read short stories.

00:51:35.590 --> 00:51:36.730 align:middle line:90%
It's a stupid title.

00:51:36.730 --> 00:51:37.650 align:middle line:90%
It's not sexy.

00:51:37.650 --> 00:51:38.880 align:middle line:90%
It's not edgy.

00:51:38.880 --> 00:51:43.170 align:middle line:84%
And if we'd given up after 100,
I'd not be sitting here today.

00:51:43.170 --> 00:51:47.900 align:middle line:84%
That's led now to 225 books
with over 500 million copies

00:51:47.900 --> 00:51:51.340 align:middle line:84%
sold in 47 languages
around the world.

00:51:51.340 --> 00:51:54.176 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely changed my life.

00:51:54.176 --> 00:51:56.010 align:middle line:84%
I've met some of the
most amazing people.

00:51:56.010 --> 00:51:57.994 align:middle line:84%
I've had lunch at
the White House.

00:51:57.994 --> 00:51:58.910 align:middle line:90%
I've met Bill Clinton.

00:51:58.910 --> 00:52:00.460 align:middle line:90%
I've met George Bush.

00:52:00.460 --> 00:52:03.155 align:middle line:84%
I've met the king of
several countries.

00:52:03.155 --> 00:52:04.730 align:middle line:84%
I've met the presidents
of countries.

00:52:04.730 --> 00:52:06.270 align:middle line:84%
I met the guys who
started Google.

00:52:06.270 --> 00:52:09.360 align:middle line:84%
So it's given me an ability
to influence, to get

00:52:09.360 --> 00:52:12.220 align:middle line:84%
into government, to make
a difference in politics,

00:52:12.220 --> 00:52:14.727 align:middle line:90%
to have a lot of things.

00:52:14.727 --> 00:52:16.310 align:middle line:84%
But the most important
thing it does--

00:52:16.310 --> 00:52:19.610 align:middle line:84%
and those are all wonderful
perks, prestige, and power,

00:52:19.610 --> 00:52:24.045 align:middle line:84%
and profits, and the big P's--
but the real big one is impact

00:52:24.045 --> 00:52:25.110 align:middle line:90%
in other people's lives.

00:52:25.110 --> 00:52:32.710 align:middle line:90%


00:52:32.710 --> 00:52:37.573 align:middle line:84%
What I have here, these are just
letters and cards thanking me

00:52:37.573 --> 00:52:39.860 align:middle line:84%
for everything from
books I've written

00:52:39.860 --> 00:52:42.320 align:middle line:90%
to seminars I've created.

00:52:42.320 --> 00:52:44.150 align:middle line:90%
Here's one from China.

00:52:44.150 --> 00:52:47.110 align:middle line:84%
I get letters, and
emails, and presents,

00:52:47.110 --> 00:52:48.620 align:middle line:84%
and books other
people have written,

00:52:48.620 --> 00:52:52.120 align:middle line:84%
and bottles of wine every
single day, saying you

00:52:52.120 --> 00:52:53.110 align:middle line:90%
changed my life.

00:52:53.110 --> 00:52:57.160 align:middle line:84%
And I think about, wow, my
book impacted that life.

00:52:57.160 --> 00:53:00.340 align:middle line:84%
And literally thousands and
thousands of stories of people

00:53:00.340 --> 00:53:03.180 align:middle line:84%
who've started businesses,
written their books.

00:53:03.180 --> 00:53:06.340 align:middle line:84%
And to know that thousands
of people around the world

00:53:06.340 --> 00:53:10.210 align:middle line:84%
have better lives because
of what I chose to write,

00:53:10.210 --> 00:53:12.331 align:middle line:90%
that's the payoff.

00:53:12.331 --> 00:53:14.580 align:middle line:84%
So at this stage of my career,
what I've decided to do

00:53:14.580 --> 00:53:16.610 align:middle line:84%
is to really focus
a lot of my energy

00:53:16.610 --> 00:53:19.860 align:middle line:84%
on helping other authors get
their message out and become

00:53:19.860 --> 00:53:21.380 align:middle line:90%
bestselling authors as well.

00:53:21.380 --> 00:53:23.000 align:middle line:84%
As I thought about
that, I said, well,

00:53:23.000 --> 00:53:26.160 align:middle line:84%
who do I know that's been in
my career that's helped me?

00:53:26.160 --> 00:53:29.050 align:middle line:84%
Some of my co-author
friends, some of my friends

00:53:29.050 --> 00:53:31.140 align:middle line:84%
who are celebrity authors,
some of the people

00:53:31.140 --> 00:53:32.820 align:middle line:84%
that helped me like
Steve Harrison.

00:53:32.820 --> 00:53:35.020 align:middle line:84%
When we started "Chicken
soup For The Soul,"

00:53:35.020 --> 00:53:37.150 align:middle line:84%
we reached out to
Steve and said, hey,

00:53:37.150 --> 00:53:39.240 align:middle line:84%
can you help us get
this book out there?

00:53:39.240 --> 00:53:42.100 align:middle line:84%
And he quantum leaped
our success very quickly.

00:53:42.100 --> 00:53:44.800 align:middle line:84%
And so I said, Steve, would you
be willing to team up with me,

00:53:44.800 --> 00:53:46.870 align:middle line:84%
and let's create a
training program that can

00:53:46.870 --> 00:53:48.500 align:middle line:90%
help authors get there faster?

00:53:48.500 --> 00:53:49.290 align:middle line:90%
And he said, yes.

00:53:49.290 --> 00:53:50.250 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVE HARRISON:
Most people who

00:53:50.250 --> 00:53:52.680 align:middle line:84%
want to succeed as authors
don't realize there really

00:53:52.680 --> 00:53:55.770 align:middle line:84%
is a marketing game, and there
are proven strategies you

00:53:55.770 --> 00:53:59.050 align:middle line:84%
can use to get more publicity
and sell a lot of books.

00:53:59.050 --> 00:54:02.110 align:middle line:84%
And Jack and I have
really enjoyed teaming up

00:54:02.110 --> 00:54:06.230 align:middle line:84%
to really share the best
seller blueprint with aspiring

00:54:06.230 --> 00:54:07.015 align:middle line:90%
authors.

00:54:07.015 --> 00:54:08.500 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD:
Everybody has a book,

00:54:08.500 --> 00:54:10.850 align:middle line:84%
whether it's a
memoir, or a cookbook,

00:54:10.850 --> 00:54:13.570 align:middle line:84%
or a book about how you were
successful as a teacher,

00:54:13.570 --> 00:54:14.520 align:middle line:90%
a real estate agent.

00:54:14.520 --> 00:54:16.280 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it might
be, there's something

00:54:16.280 --> 00:54:19.065 align:middle line:84%
you have to share with the
world that's uniquely yours.

00:54:19.065 --> 00:54:20.670 align:middle line:90%
And here's the deal.

00:54:20.670 --> 00:54:22.620 align:middle line:90%
You just have to start.

00:54:22.620 --> 00:54:25.157 align:middle line:84%
You sit down, and
you write one page,

00:54:25.157 --> 00:54:26.740 align:middle line:84%
then you write a
second page, and then

00:54:26.740 --> 00:54:28.160 align:middle line:90%
you write a third page.

00:54:28.160 --> 00:54:29.850 align:middle line:90%
Now it's easy to say that.

00:54:29.850 --> 00:54:32.400 align:middle line:84%
There's some skills that
are useful to do that.

00:54:32.400 --> 00:54:34.474 align:middle line:90%
We can teach you how to do that.

00:54:34.474 --> 00:54:36.140 align:middle line:84%
We can give you the
confidence to do it.

00:54:36.140 --> 00:54:37.750 align:middle line:84%
We can give you the
skills to do it.

00:54:37.750 --> 00:54:39.650 align:middle line:84%
We can give you the
support to keep doing it

00:54:39.650 --> 00:54:41.360 align:middle line:84%
until you get it done,
and then teach you

00:54:41.360 --> 00:54:44.070 align:middle line:84%
how to get the book out there
so people actually read it.

00:54:44.070 --> 00:54:46.289 align:middle line:84%
And you, my friend,
have a huge impact

00:54:46.289 --> 00:54:47.830 align:middle line:84%
in the world that's
going to give you

00:54:47.830 --> 00:54:49.005 align:middle line:84%
a sense of meaning
and fulfillment

00:54:49.005 --> 00:54:50.593 align:middle line:84%
that you can't
even imagine today.

00:54:50.593 --> 00:54:53.251 align:middle line:90%


00:54:53.251 --> 00:54:55.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you've
impacted someone's life.

00:54:55.350 --> 00:54:58.210 align:middle line:84%
They decide they want to write
their story like my friend who

00:54:58.210 --> 00:55:00.490 align:middle line:84%
had that accident on
the beach and went

00:55:00.490 --> 00:55:01.730 align:middle line:90%
in and out of those lives.

00:55:01.730 --> 00:55:03.120 align:middle line:84%
He could write
that story, right?

00:55:03.120 --> 00:55:03.770 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Yeah.

00:55:03.770 --> 00:55:04.978 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How would he do that?

00:55:04.978 --> 00:55:07.567 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: Well, the writing
of it there's, a lot of ways.

00:55:07.567 --> 00:55:09.400 align:middle line:84%
Number one, you can
just sit down the write.

00:55:09.400 --> 00:55:11.560 align:middle line:84%
Number two, you can have
someone interview you,

00:55:11.560 --> 00:55:14.660 align:middle line:84%
because often we don't know what
we know until someone asks us.

00:55:14.660 --> 00:55:16.400 align:middle line:84%
You could record
it into a recorder

00:55:16.400 --> 00:55:19.710 align:middle line:84%
and have someone in Sri
Lanka or fiverr.com,

00:55:19.710 --> 00:55:22.130 align:middle line:90%
whatever, type it for you.

00:55:22.130 --> 00:55:24.900 align:middle line:84%
My wife's writing an episodic
memoir right now by doing that.

00:55:24.900 --> 00:55:26.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of her life?

00:55:26.180 --> 00:55:26.570 align:middle line:90%
>>CANFIELD: Of her life.

00:55:26.570 --> 00:55:27.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: With you?

00:55:27.360 --> 00:55:28.620 align:middle line:84%
>>CANFIELD: No, just
of her own life.

00:55:28.620 --> 00:55:29.260 align:middle line:90%
Not with me.

00:55:29.260 --> 00:55:32.040 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm part if it,
but from childhood.

00:55:32.040 --> 00:55:35.160 align:middle line:84%
The key thing is once you get--
I always recommend people just

00:55:35.160 --> 00:55:36.619 align:middle line:90%
sit down and outline it first.

00:55:36.619 --> 00:55:38.160 align:middle line:84%
Dot points, whatever
you want to say.

00:55:38.160 --> 00:55:41.010 align:middle line:84%
And then you can speak into that
and put more my words on it.

00:55:41.010 --> 00:55:42.435 align:middle line:84%
But the key thing
is-- and this is

00:55:42.435 --> 00:55:44.370 align:middle line:84%
what made "Chicken
Soup" so successful--

00:55:44.370 --> 00:55:47.510 align:middle line:84%
get at least 10 other people to
read it and give you feedback.

00:55:47.510 --> 00:55:50.490 align:middle line:84%
Literally, page by page,
chapter by chapter, what works,

00:55:50.490 --> 00:55:51.330 align:middle line:90%
what doesn't.

00:55:51.330 --> 00:55:54.040 align:middle line:84%
On a scale of 1 to 10,
would you rate it a 10?

00:55:54.040 --> 00:55:55.535 align:middle line:84%
Anything less than
a 10, it's a 7,

00:55:55.535 --> 00:55:57.660 align:middle line:84%
what would it take
to make it a 10?

00:55:57.660 --> 00:56:00.750 align:middle line:84%
Too redundant, there's
self-disclosure, your preaching

00:56:00.750 --> 00:56:01.867 align:middle line:90%
at me, whatever it is.

00:56:01.867 --> 00:56:03.700 align:middle line:84%
And that's what made
"Chicken Soup" so good.

00:56:03.700 --> 00:56:06.610 align:middle line:84%
The first version, we
had 40 people read it,

00:56:06.610 --> 00:56:07.635 align:middle line:90%
give us feedback.

00:56:07.635 --> 00:56:10.010 align:middle line:84%
My sister said take out all
the preachy stuff at the end,

00:56:10.010 --> 00:56:11.343 align:middle line:90%
and don't tell me what to think.

00:56:11.343 --> 00:56:11.970 align:middle line:90%
And we did.

